  47 def _get_concat_variable(name, shape, dtype, num_shards):
  48   """Get a sharded variable concatenated into one tensor."""
  49   sharded_variable = _get_sharded_variable(name, shape, dtype, num_shards)
  50   if len(sharded_variable) == 1:
  51     return sharded_variable[0]
  52 
  53   concat_name = name + "/concat"
  54   concat_full_name = vs.get_variable_scope().name + "/" + concat_name + ":0"
  55   for value in ops.get_collection(ops.GraphKeys.CONCATENATED_VARIABLES):
  56     if value.name == concat_full_name:
  57       return value
  58 
  59   concat_variable = array_ops.concat(sharded_variable, 0, name=concat_name)
  60   ops.add_to_collection(ops.GraphKeys.CONCATENATED_VARIABLES, concat_variable)
  61   return concat_variable
  62 
  63 
  64 def _get_sharded_variable(name, shape, dtype, num_shards):
  65   """Get a list of sharded variables with the given dtype."""
  66   if num_shards > shape[0]:
  67     raise ValueError("Too many shards: shape=%s, num_shards=%d" % (shape,
  68                                                                    num_shards))
  69   unit_shard_size = int(math.floor(shape[0] / num_shards))
  70   remaining_rows = shape[0] - unit_shard_size * num_shards
  71 
  72   shards = []
  73   for i in range(num_shards):
  74     current_size = unit_shard_size
  75     if i < remaining_rows:
  76       current_size += 1
  77     shards.append(
  78         vs.get_variable(
  79             name + "_%d" % i, [current_size] + shape[1:], dtype=dtype))
  80   return shards
  81 
  82 
  83 def _norm(g, b, inp, scope):
  84   shape = inp.get_shape()[-1:]
  85   gamma_init = init_ops.constant_initializer(g)
  86   beta_init = init_ops.constant_initializer(b)
  87   with vs.variable_scope(scope):
  88     # Initialize beta and gamma for use by layer_norm.
  89     vs.get_variable("gamma", shape=shape, initializer=gamma_init)
  90     vs.get_variable("beta", shape=shape, initializer=beta_init)
  91   normalized = layers.layer_norm(inp, reuse=True, scope=scope)
  92   return normalized
  93

  95 class CoupledInputForgetGateLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
  96   """Long short-term memory unit (LSTM) recurrent network cell.
  97 
  98   The default non-peephole implementation is based on:
  99 
 100     https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/1154/0131eae85b2e11d53df7f1360eeb6476e7f4.pdf
 101 
 102   Felix Gers, Jurgen Schmidhuber, and Fred Cummins.
 103   "Learning to forget: Continual prediction with LSTM." IET, 850-855, 1999.
 104 
 105   The peephole implementation is based on:
 106 
 107     https://research.google.com/pubs/archive/43905.pdf
 108 
 109   Hasim Sak, Andrew Senior, and Francoise Beaufays.
 110   "Long short-term memory recurrent neural network architectures for
 111    large scale acoustic modeling." INTERSPEECH, 2014.
 112 
 113   The coupling of input and forget gate is based on:
 114 
 115     http://arxiv.org/pdf/1503.04069.pdf
 116 
 117   Greff et al. "LSTM: A Search Space Odyssey"
 118 
 119   The class uses optional peep-hole connections, and an optional projection
 120   layer.
 121   Layer normalization implementation is based on:
 122 
 123     https://arxiv.org/abs/1607.06450.
 124 
 125   "Layer Normalization"
 126   Jimmy Lei Ba, Jamie Ryan Kiros, Geoffrey E. Hinton
 127 
 128   and is applied before the internal nonlinearities.
 129 
 130   """
 131 
 132   def __init__(self,
 133                num_units,
 134                use_peepholes=False,
 135                initializer=None,
 136                num_proj=None,
 137                proj_clip=None,
 138                num_unit_shards=1,
 139                num_proj_shards=1,
 140                forget_bias=1.0,
 141                state_is_tuple=True,
 142                activation=math_ops.tanh,
 143                reuse=None,
 144                layer_norm=False,
 145                norm_gain=1.0,
 146                norm_shift=0.0):
 147     """Initialize the parameters for an LSTM cell.
 148 
 149     Args:
 150       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
 151       use_peepholes: bool, set True to enable diagonal/peephole connections.
 152       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
 153         projection matrices.
 154       num_proj: (optional) int, The output dimensionality for the projection
 155         matrices.  If None, no projection is performed.
 156       proj_clip: (optional) A float value.  If `num_proj > 0` and `proj_clip` is
 157       provided, then the projected values are clipped elementwise to within
 158       `[-proj_clip, proj_clip]`.
 159       num_unit_shards: How to split the weight matrix.  If >1, the weight
 160         matrix is stored across num_unit_shards.
 161       num_proj_shards: How to split the projection matrix.  If >1, the
 162         projection matrix is stored across num_proj_shards.
 163       forget_bias: Biases of the forget gate are initialized by default to 1
 164         in order to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning of
 165         the training.
 166       state_is_tuple: If True, accepted and returned states are 2-tuples of
 167         the `c_state` and `m_state`.  By default (False), they are concatenated
 168         along the column axis.  This default behavior will soon be deprecated.
 169       activation: Activation function of the inner states.
 170       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
 171         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
 172         the given variables, an error is raised.
 173       layer_norm: If `True`, layer normalization will be applied.
 174       norm_gain: float, The layer normalization gain initial value. If
 175         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
 176       norm_shift: float, The layer normalization shift initial value. If
 177         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
 178     """
 179     super(CoupledInputForgetGateLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
 180     if not state_is_tuple:
 181       logging.warn("%s: Using a concatenated state is slower and will soon be "
 182                    "deprecated.  Use state_is_tuple=True.", self)
 183     self._num_units = num_units
 184     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
 185     self._initializer = initializer
 186     self._num_proj = num_proj
 187     self._proj_clip = proj_clip
 188     self._num_unit_shards = num_unit_shards
 189     self._num_proj_shards = num_proj_shards
 190     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
 191     self._state_is_tuple = state_is_tuple
 192     self._activation = activation
 193     self._reuse = reuse
 194     self._layer_norm = layer_norm
 195     self._norm_gain = norm_gain
 196     self._norm_shift = norm_shift
 197 
 198     if num_proj:
 199       self._state_size = (
 200           rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_proj)
 201           if state_is_tuple else num_units + num_proj)
 202       self._output_size = num_proj
 203     else:
 204       self._state_size = (
 205           rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_units)
 206           if state_is_tuple else 2 * num_units)
 207       self._output_size = num_units
 208 
 209   @property
 210   def state_size(self):
 211     return self._state_size
 212 
 213   @property
 214   def output_size(self):
 215     return self._output_size
 216 
 217   def call(self, inputs, state):
 218     """Run one step of LSTM.
 219 
 220     Args:
 221       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
 222       state: if `state_is_tuple` is False, this must be a state Tensor,
 223         `2-D, batch x state_size`.  If `state_is_tuple` is True, this must be a
 224         tuple of state Tensors, both `2-D`, with column sizes `c_state` and
 225         `m_state`.
 226 
 227     Returns:
 228       A tuple containing:
 229       - A `2-D, [batch x output_dim]`, Tensor representing the output of the
 230         LSTM after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
 231         Here output_dim is:
 232            num_proj if num_proj was set,
 233            num_units otherwise.
 234       - Tensor(s) representing the new state of LSTM after reading `inputs` when
 235         the previous state was `state`.  Same type and shape(s) as `state`.
 236 
 237     Raises:
 238       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
 239         static shape inference.
 240     """
 241     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
 242 
 243     num_proj = self._num_units if self._num_proj is None else self._num_proj
 244 
 245     if self._state_is_tuple:
 246       (c_prev, m_prev) = state
 247     else:
 248       c_prev = array_ops.slice(state, [0, 0], [-1, self._num_units])
 249       m_prev = array_ops.slice(state, [0, self._num_units], [-1, num_proj])
 250 
 251     dtype = inputs.dtype
 252     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
 253     if input_size.value is None:
 254       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
 255     concat_w = _get_concat_variable(
 256         "W", [input_size.value + num_proj, 3 * self._num_units], dtype,
 257         self._num_unit_shards)
 258 
 259     b = vs.get_variable(
 260         "B",
 261         shape=[3 * self._num_units],
 262         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 263         dtype=dtype)
 264 
 265     # j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
 266     cell_inputs = array_ops.concat([inputs, m_prev], 1)
 267     lstm_matrix = math_ops.matmul(cell_inputs, concat_w)
 268 
 269     # If layer nomalization is applied, do not add bias
 270     if not self._layer_norm:
 271       lstm_matrix = nn_ops.bias_add(lstm_matrix, b)
 272 
 273     j, f, o = array_ops.split(value=lstm_matrix, num_or_size_splits=3, axis=1)
 274 
 275     # Apply layer normalization
 276     if self._layer_norm:
 277       j = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, j, "transform")
 278       f = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, f, "forget")
 279       o = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, o, "output")
 280 
 281     # Diagonal connections
 282     if self._use_peepholes:
 283       w_f_diag = vs.get_variable(
 284           "W_F_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 285       w_o_diag = vs.get_variable(
 286           "W_O_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 287 
 288     if self._use_peepholes:
 289       f_act = sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag * c_prev)
 290     else:
 291       f_act = sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias)
 292     c = (f_act * c_prev + (1 - f_act) * self._activation(j))
 293 
 294     # Apply layer normalization
 295     if self._layer_norm:
 296       c = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, c, "state")
 297 
 298     if self._use_peepholes:
 299       m = sigmoid(o + w_o_diag * c) * self._activation(c)
 300     else:
 301       m = sigmoid(o) * self._activation(c)
 302 
 303     if self._num_proj is not None:
 304       concat_w_proj = _get_concat_variable("W_P",
 305                                            [self._num_units, self._num_proj],
 306                                            dtype, self._num_proj_shards)
 307 
 308       m = math_ops.matmul(m, concat_w_proj)
 309       if self._proj_clip is not None:
 310         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 311         m = clip_ops.clip_by_value(m, -self._proj_clip, self._proj_clip)
 312         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 313 
 314     new_state = (
 315         rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(c, m)
 316         if self._state_is_tuple else array_ops.concat([c, m], 1))
 317     return m, new_state
 318 
 319 
 320 class TimeFreqLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
 321   """Time-Frequency Long short-term memory unit (LSTM) recurrent network cell.
 322 
 323   This implementation is based on:
 324 
 325     Tara N. Sainath and Bo Li
 326     "Modeling Time-Frequency Patterns with LSTM vs. Convolutional Architectures
 327     for LVCSR Tasks." submitted to INTERSPEECH, 2016.
 328 
 329   It uses peep-hole connections and optional cell clipping.
 330   """
 331 
 332   def __init__(self,
 333                num_units,
 334                use_peepholes=False,
 335                cell_clip=None,
 336                initializer=None,
 337                num_unit_shards=1,
 338                forget_bias=1.0,
 339                feature_size=None,
 340                frequency_skip=1,
 341                reuse=None):
 342     """Initialize the parameters for an LSTM cell.
 343 
 344     Args:
 345       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
 346       use_peepholes: bool, set True to enable diagonal/peephole connections.
 347       cell_clip: (optional) A float value, if provided the cell state is clipped
 348         by this value prior to the cell output activation.
 349       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
 350         projection matrices.
 351       num_unit_shards: int, How to split the weight matrix.  If >1, the weight
 352         matrix is stored across num_unit_shards.
 353       forget_bias: float, Biases of the forget gate are initialized by default
 354         to 1 in order to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning
 355         of the training.
 356       feature_size: int, The size of the input feature the LSTM spans over.
 357       frequency_skip: int, The amount the LSTM filter is shifted by in
 358         frequency.
 359       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
 360         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
 361         the given variables, an error is raised.
 362     """
 363     super(TimeFreqLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
 364     self._num_units = num_units
 365     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
 366     self._cell_clip = cell_clip
 367     self._initializer = initializer
 368     self._num_unit_shards = num_unit_shards
 369     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
 370     self._feature_size = feature_size
 371     self._frequency_skip = frequency_skip
 372     self._state_size = 2 * num_units
 373     self._output_size = num_units
 374     self._reuse = reuse
 375 
 376   @property
 377   def output_size(self):
 378     return self._output_size
 379 
 380   @property
 381   def state_size(self):
 382     return self._state_size
 383 
 384   def call(self, inputs, state):
 385     """Run one step of LSTM.
 386 
 387     Args:
 388       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
 389       state: state Tensor, 2D, batch x state_size.
 390 
 391     Returns:
 392       A tuple containing:
 393       - A 2D, batch x output_dim, Tensor representing the output of the LSTM
 394         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
 395         Here output_dim is num_units.
 396       - A 2D, batch x state_size, Tensor representing the new state of LSTM
 397         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
 398     Raises:
 399       ValueError: if an input_size was specified and the provided inputs have
 400         a different dimension.
 401     """
 402     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
 403     tanh = math_ops.tanh
 404 
 405     freq_inputs = self._make_tf_features(inputs)
 406     dtype = inputs.dtype
 407     actual_input_size = freq_inputs[0].get_shape().as_list()[1]
 408 
 409     concat_w = _get_concat_variable(
 410         "W", [actual_input_size + 2 * self._num_units, 4 * self._num_units],
 411         dtype, self._num_unit_shards)
 412 
 413     b = vs.get_variable(
 414         "B",
 415         shape=[4 * self._num_units],
 416         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 417         dtype=dtype)
 418 
 419     # Diagonal connections
 420     if self._use_peepholes:
 421       w_f_diag = vs.get_variable(
 422           "W_F_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 423       w_i_diag = vs.get_variable(
 424           "W_I_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 425       w_o_diag = vs.get_variable(
 426           "W_O_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 427 
 428     # initialize the first freq state to be zero
 429     m_prev_freq = array_ops.zeros(
 430         [inputs.shape[0].value or inputs.get_shape()[0], self._num_units],
 431         dtype)
 432     for fq in range(len(freq_inputs)):
 433       c_prev = array_ops.slice(state, [0, 2 * fq * self._num_units],
 434                                [-1, self._num_units])
 435       m_prev = array_ops.slice(state, [0, (2 * fq + 1) * self._num_units],
 436                                [-1, self._num_units])
 437       # i = input_gate, j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
 438       cell_inputs = array_ops.concat([freq_inputs[fq], m_prev, m_prev_freq], 1)
 439       lstm_matrix = nn_ops.bias_add(math_ops.matmul(cell_inputs, concat_w), b)
 440       i, j, f, o = array_ops.split(
 441           value=lstm_matrix, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
 442 
 443       if self._use_peepholes:
 444         c = (
 445             sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag * c_prev) * c_prev +
 446             sigmoid(i + w_i_diag * c_prev) * tanh(j))
 447       else:
 448         c = (sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias) * c_prev + sigmoid(i) * tanh(j))
 449 
 450       if self._cell_clip is not None:
 451         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 452         c = clip_ops.clip_by_value(c, -self._cell_clip, self._cell_clip)
 453         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 454 
 455       if self._use_peepholes:
 456         m = sigmoid(o + w_o_diag * c) * tanh(c)
 457       else:
 458         m = sigmoid(o) * tanh(c)
 459       m_prev_freq = m
 460       if fq == 0:
 461         state_out = array_ops.concat([c, m], 1)
 462         m_out = m
 463       else:
 464         state_out = array_ops.concat([state_out, c, m], 1)
 465         m_out = array_ops.concat([m_out, m], 1)
 466     return m_out, state_out
 467 
 468   def _make_tf_features(self, input_feat):
 469     """Make the frequency features.
 470 
 471     Args:
 472       input_feat: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
 473 
 474     Returns:
 475       A list of frequency features, with each element containing:
 476       - A 2D, batch x output_dim, Tensor representing the time-frequency feature
 477         for that frequency index. Here output_dim is feature_size.
 478     Raises:
 479       ValueError: if input_size cannot be inferred from static shape inference.
 480     """
 481     input_size = input_feat.get_shape().with_rank(2)[-1].value
 482     if input_size is None:
 483       raise ValueError("Cannot infer input_size from static shape inference.")
 484     num_feats = int(
 485         (input_size - self._feature_size) / (self._frequency_skip)) + 1
 486     freq_inputs = []
 487     for f in range(num_feats):
 488       cur_input = array_ops.slice(input_feat, [0, f * self._frequency_skip],
 489                                   [-1, self._feature_size])
 490       freq_inputs.append(cur_input)
 491     return freq_inputs
 492 
 493 
 494 class GridLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
 495   """Grid Long short-term memory unit (LSTM) recurrent network cell.
 496 
 497   The default is based on:
 498     Nal Kalchbrenner, Ivo Danihelka and Alex Graves
 499     "Grid Long Short-Term Memory," Proc. ICLR 2016.
 500     http://arxiv.org/abs/1507.01526
 501 
 502   When peephole connections are used, the implementation is based on:
 503     Tara N. Sainath and Bo Li
 504     "Modeling Time-Frequency Patterns with LSTM vs. Convolutional Architectures
 505     for LVCSR Tasks." submitted to INTERSPEECH, 2016.
 506 
 507   The code uses optional peephole connections, shared_weights and cell clipping.
 508   """
 509 
 510   def __init__(self,
 511                num_units,
 512                use_peepholes=False,
 513                share_time_frequency_weights=False,
 514                cell_clip=None,
 515                initializer=None,
 516                num_unit_shards=1,
 517                forget_bias=1.0,
 518                feature_size=None,
 519                frequency_skip=None,
 520                num_frequency_blocks=None,
 521                start_freqindex_list=None,
 522                end_freqindex_list=None,
 523                couple_input_forget_gates=False,
 524                state_is_tuple=True,
 525                reuse=None):
 526     """Initialize the parameters for an LSTM cell.
 527 
 528     Args:
 529       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
 530       use_peepholes: (optional) bool, default False. Set True to enable
 531         diagonal/peephole connections.
 532       share_time_frequency_weights: (optional) bool, default False. Set True to
 533         enable shared cell weights between time and frequency LSTMs.
 534       cell_clip: (optional) A float value, default None, if provided the cell
 535         state is clipped by this value prior to the cell output activation.
 536       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
 537         projection matrices, default None.
 538       num_unit_shards: (optional) int, default 1, How to split the weight
 539         matrix. If > 1, the weight matrix is stored across num_unit_shards.
 540       forget_bias: (optional) float, default 1.0, The initial bias of the
 541         forget gates, used to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning
 542         of the training.
 543       feature_size: (optional) int, default None, The size of the input feature
 544         the LSTM spans over.
 545       frequency_skip: (optional) int, default None, The amount the LSTM filter
 546         is shifted by in frequency.
 547       num_frequency_blocks: [required] A list of frequency blocks needed to
 548         cover the whole input feature splitting defined by start_freqindex_list
 549         and end_freqindex_list.
 550       start_freqindex_list: [optional], list of ints, default None,  The
 551         starting frequency index for each frequency block.
 552       end_freqindex_list: [optional], list of ints, default None. The ending
 553         frequency index for each frequency block.
 554       couple_input_forget_gates: (optional) bool, default False, Whether to
 555         couple the input and forget gates, i.e. f_gate = 1.0 - i_gate, to reduce
 556         model parameters and computation cost.
 557       state_is_tuple: If True, accepted and returned states are 2-tuples of
 558         the `c_state` and `m_state`.  By default (False), they are concatenated
 559         along the column axis.  This default behavior will soon be deprecated.
 560       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
 561         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
 562         the given variables, an error is raised.
 563     Raises:
 564       ValueError: if the num_frequency_blocks list is not specified
 565     """
 566     super(GridLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
 567     if not state_is_tuple:
 568       logging.warn("%s: Using a concatenated state is slower and will soon be "
 569                    "deprecated.  Use state_is_tuple=True.", self)
 570     self._num_units = num_units
 571     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
 572     self._share_time_frequency_weights = share_time_frequency_weights
 573     self._couple_input_forget_gates = couple_input_forget_gates
 574     self._state_is_tuple = state_is_tuple
 575     self._cell_clip = cell_clip
 576     self._initializer = initializer
 577     self._num_unit_shards = num_unit_shards
 578     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
 579     self._feature_size = feature_size
 580     self._frequency_skip = frequency_skip
 581     self._start_freqindex_list = start_freqindex_list
 582     self._end_freqindex_list = end_freqindex_list
 583     self._num_frequency_blocks = num_frequency_blocks
 584     self._total_blocks = 0
 585     self._reuse = reuse
 586     if self._num_frequency_blocks is None:
 587       raise ValueError("Must specify num_frequency_blocks")
 588 
 589     for block_index in range(len(self._num_frequency_blocks)):
 590       self._total_blocks += int(self._num_frequency_blocks[block_index])
 591     if state_is_tuple:
 592       state_names = ""
 593       for block_index in range(len(self._num_frequency_blocks)):
 594         for freq_index in range(self._num_frequency_blocks[block_index]):
 595           name_prefix = "state_f%02d_b%02d" % (freq_index, block_index)
 596           state_names += ("%s_c, %s_m," % (name_prefix, name_prefix))
 597       self._state_tuple_type = collections.namedtuple("GridLSTMStateTuple",
 598                                                       state_names.strip(","))
 599       self._state_size = self._state_tuple_type(*(
 600           [num_units, num_units] * self._total_blocks))
 601     else:
 602       self._state_tuple_type = None
 603       self._state_size = num_units * self._total_blocks * 2
 604     self._output_size = num_units * self._total_blocks * 2
 605 
 606   @property
 607   def output_size(self):
 608     return self._output_size
 609 
 610   @property
 611   def state_size(self):
 612     return self._state_size
 613 
 614   @property
 615   def state_tuple_type(self):
 616     return self._state_tuple_type
 617 
 618   def call(self, inputs, state):
 619     """Run one step of LSTM.
 620 
 621     Args:
 622       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, [batch, feature_size].
 623       state: Tensor or tuple of Tensors, 2D, [batch, state_size], depends on the
 624         flag self._state_is_tuple.
 625 
 626     Returns:
 627       A tuple containing:
 628       - A 2D, [batch, output_dim], Tensor representing the output of the LSTM
 629         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
 630         Here output_dim is num_units.
 631       - A 2D, [batch, state_size], Tensor representing the new state of LSTM
 632         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
 633     Raises:
 634       ValueError: if an input_size was specified and the provided inputs have
 635         a different dimension.
 636     """
 637     batch_size = inputs.shape[0].value or array_ops.shape(inputs)[0]
 638     freq_inputs = self._make_tf_features(inputs)
 639     m_out_lst = []
 640     state_out_lst = []
 641     for block in range(len(freq_inputs)):
 642       m_out_lst_current, state_out_lst_current = self._compute(
 643           freq_inputs[block],
 644           block,
 645           state,
 646           batch_size,
 647           state_is_tuple=self._state_is_tuple)
 648       m_out_lst.extend(m_out_lst_current)
 649       state_out_lst.extend(state_out_lst_current)
 650     if self._state_is_tuple:
 651       state_out = self._state_tuple_type(*state_out_lst)
 652     else:
 653       state_out = array_ops.concat(state_out_lst, 1)
 654     m_out = array_ops.concat(m_out_lst, 1)
 655     return m_out, state_out
 656 
 657   def _compute(self,
 658                freq_inputs,
 659                block,
 660                state,
 661                batch_size,
 662                state_prefix="state",
 663                state_is_tuple=True):
 664     """Run the actual computation of one step LSTM.
 665 
 666     Args:
 667       freq_inputs: list of Tensors, 2D, [batch, feature_size].
 668       block: int, current frequency block index to process.
 669       state: Tensor or tuple of Tensors, 2D, [batch, state_size], it depends on
 670         the flag state_is_tuple.
 671       batch_size: int32, batch size.
 672       state_prefix: (optional) string, name prefix for states, defaults to
 673         "state".
 674       state_is_tuple: boolean, indicates whether the state is a tuple or Tensor.
 675 
 676     Returns:
 677       A tuple, containing:
 678       - A list of [batch, output_dim] Tensors, representing the output of the
 679         LSTM given the inputs and state.
 680       - A list of [batch, state_size] Tensors, representing the LSTM state
 681         values given the inputs and previous state.
 682     """
 683     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
 684     tanh = math_ops.tanh
 685     num_gates = 3 if self._couple_input_forget_gates else 4
 686     dtype = freq_inputs[0].dtype
 687     actual_input_size = freq_inputs[0].get_shape().as_list()[1]
 688 
 689     concat_w_f = _get_concat_variable(
 690         "W_f_%d" % block,
 691         [actual_input_size + 2 * self._num_units, num_gates * self._num_units],
 692         dtype, self._num_unit_shards)
 693     b_f = vs.get_variable(
 694         "B_f_%d" % block,
 695         shape=[num_gates * self._num_units],
 696         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 697         dtype=dtype)
 698     if not self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 699       concat_w_t = _get_concat_variable("W_t_%d" % block, [
 700           actual_input_size + 2 * self._num_units, num_gates * self._num_units
 701       ], dtype, self._num_unit_shards)
 702       b_t = vs.get_variable(
 703           "B_t_%d" % block,
 704           shape=[num_gates * self._num_units],
 705           initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
 706           dtype=dtype)
 707 
 708     if self._use_peepholes:
 709       # Diagonal connections
 710       if not self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 711         w_f_diag_freqf = vs.get_variable(
 712             "W_F_diag_freqf_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 713         w_f_diag_freqt = vs.get_variable(
 714             "W_F_diag_freqt_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 715       w_i_diag_freqf = vs.get_variable(
 716           "W_I_diag_freqf_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 717       w_i_diag_freqt = vs.get_variable(
 718           "W_I_diag_freqt_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 719       w_o_diag_freqf = vs.get_variable(
 720           "W_O_diag_freqf_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 721       w_o_diag_freqt = vs.get_variable(
 722           "W_O_diag_freqt_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 723       if not self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 724         if not self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 725           w_f_diag_timef = vs.get_variable(
 726               "W_F_diag_timef_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 727           w_f_diag_timet = vs.get_variable(
 728               "W_F_diag_timet_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 729         w_i_diag_timef = vs.get_variable(
 730             "W_I_diag_timef_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 731         w_i_diag_timet = vs.get_variable(
 732             "W_I_diag_timet_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 733         w_o_diag_timef = vs.get_variable(
 734             "W_O_diag_timef_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 735         w_o_diag_timet = vs.get_variable(
 736             "W_O_diag_timet_%d" % block, shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
 737 
 738     # initialize the first freq state to be zero
 739     m_prev_freq = array_ops.zeros([batch_size, self._num_units], dtype)
 740     c_prev_freq = array_ops.zeros([batch_size, self._num_units], dtype)
 741     for freq_index in range(len(freq_inputs)):
 742       if state_is_tuple:
 743         name_prefix = "%s_f%02d_b%02d" % (state_prefix, freq_index, block)
 744         c_prev_time = getattr(state, name_prefix + "_c")
 745         m_prev_time = getattr(state, name_prefix + "_m")
 746       else:
 747         c_prev_time = array_ops.slice(
 748             state, [0, 2 * freq_index * self._num_units], [-1, self._num_units])
 749         m_prev_time = array_ops.slice(
 750             state, [0, (2 * freq_index + 1) * self._num_units],
 751             [-1, self._num_units])
 752 
 753       # i = input_gate, j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
 754       cell_inputs = array_ops.concat(
 755           [freq_inputs[freq_index], m_prev_time, m_prev_freq], 1)
 756 
 757       # F-LSTM
 758       lstm_matrix_freq = nn_ops.bias_add(
 759           math_ops.matmul(cell_inputs, concat_w_f), b_f)
 760       if self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 761         i_freq, j_freq, o_freq = array_ops.split(
 762             value=lstm_matrix_freq, num_or_size_splits=num_gates, axis=1)
 763         f_freq = None
 764       else:
 765         i_freq, j_freq, f_freq, o_freq = array_ops.split(
 766             value=lstm_matrix_freq, num_or_size_splits=num_gates, axis=1)
 767       # T-LSTM
 768       if self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 769         i_time = i_freq
 770         j_time = j_freq
 771         f_time = f_freq
 772         o_time = o_freq
 773       else:
 774         lstm_matrix_time = nn_ops.bias_add(
 775             math_ops.matmul(cell_inputs, concat_w_t), b_t)
 776         if self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 777           i_time, j_time, o_time = array_ops.split(
 778               value=lstm_matrix_time, num_or_size_splits=num_gates, axis=1)
 779           f_time = None
 780         else:
 781           i_time, j_time, f_time, o_time = array_ops.split(
 782               value=lstm_matrix_time, num_or_size_splits=num_gates, axis=1)
 783 
 784       # F-LSTM c_freq
 785       # input gate activations
 786       if self._use_peepholes:
 787         i_freq_g = sigmoid(i_freq + w_i_diag_freqf * c_prev_freq +
 788                            w_i_diag_freqt * c_prev_time)
 789       else:
 790         i_freq_g = sigmoid(i_freq)
 791       # forget gate activations
 792       if self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 793         f_freq_g = 1.0 - i_freq_g
 794       else:
 795         if self._use_peepholes:
 796           f_freq_g = sigmoid(f_freq + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag_freqf *
 797                              c_prev_freq + w_f_diag_freqt * c_prev_time)
 798         else:
 799           f_freq_g = sigmoid(f_freq + self._forget_bias)
 800       # cell state
 801       c_freq = f_freq_g * c_prev_freq + i_freq_g * tanh(j_freq)
 802       if self._cell_clip is not None:
 803         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 804         c_freq = clip_ops.clip_by_value(c_freq, -self._cell_clip,
 805                                         self._cell_clip)
 806         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 807 
 808       # T-LSTM c_freq
 809       # input gate activations
 810       if self._use_peepholes:
 811         if self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 812           i_time_g = sigmoid(i_time + w_i_diag_freqf * c_prev_freq +
 813                              w_i_diag_freqt * c_prev_time)
 814         else:
 815           i_time_g = sigmoid(i_time + w_i_diag_timef * c_prev_freq +
 816                              w_i_diag_timet * c_prev_time)
 817       else:
 818         i_time_g = sigmoid(i_time)
 819       # forget gate activations
 820       if self._couple_input_forget_gates:
 821         f_time_g = 1.0 - i_time_g
 822       else:
 823         if self._use_peepholes:
 824           if self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 825             f_time_g = sigmoid(f_time + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag_freqf *
 826                                c_prev_freq + w_f_diag_freqt * c_prev_time)
 827           else:
 828             f_time_g = sigmoid(f_time + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag_timef *
 829                                c_prev_freq + w_f_diag_timet * c_prev_time)
 830         else:
 831           f_time_g = sigmoid(f_time + self._forget_bias)
 832       # cell state
 833       c_time = f_time_g * c_prev_time + i_time_g * tanh(j_time)
 834       if self._cell_clip is not None:
 835         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 836         c_time = clip_ops.clip_by_value(c_time, -self._cell_clip,
 837                                         self._cell_clip)
 838         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
 839 
 840       # F-LSTM m_freq
 841       if self._use_peepholes:
 842         m_freq = sigmoid(o_freq + w_o_diag_freqf * c_freq +
 843                          w_o_diag_freqt * c_time) * tanh(c_freq)
 844       else:
 845         m_freq = sigmoid(o_freq) * tanh(c_freq)
 846 
 847       # T-LSTM m_time
 848       if self._use_peepholes:
 849         if self._share_time_frequency_weights:
 850           m_time = sigmoid(o_time + w_o_diag_freqf * c_freq +
 851                            w_o_diag_freqt * c_time) * tanh(c_time)
 852         else:
 853           m_time = sigmoid(o_time + w_o_diag_timef * c_freq +
 854                            w_o_diag_timet * c_time) * tanh(c_time)
 855       else:
 856         m_time = sigmoid(o_time) * tanh(c_time)
 857 
 858       m_prev_freq = m_freq
 859       c_prev_freq = c_freq
 860       # Concatenate the outputs for T-LSTM and F-LSTM for each shift
 861       if freq_index == 0:
 862         state_out_lst = [c_time, m_time]
 863         m_out_lst = [m_time, m_freq]
 864       else:
 865         state_out_lst.extend([c_time, m_time])
 866         m_out_lst.extend([m_time, m_freq])
 867 
 868     return m_out_lst, state_out_lst
 869 
 870   def _make_tf_features(self, input_feat, slice_offset=0):
 871     """Make the frequency features.
 872 
 873     Args:
 874       input_feat: input Tensor, 2D, [batch, num_units].
 875       slice_offset: (optional) Python int, default 0, the slicing offset is only
 876         used for the backward processing in the BidirectionalGridLSTMCell. It
 877         specifies a different starting point instead of always 0 to enable the
 878         forward and backward processing look at different frequency blocks.
 879 
 880     Returns:
 881       A list of frequency features, with each element containing:
 882       - A 2D, [batch, output_dim], Tensor representing the time-frequency
 883         feature for that frequency index. Here output_dim is feature_size.
 884     Raises:
 885       ValueError: if input_size cannot be inferred from static shape inference.
 886     """
 887     input_size = input_feat.get_shape().with_rank(2)[-1].value
 888     if input_size is None:
 889       raise ValueError("Cannot infer input_size from static shape inference.")
 890     if slice_offset > 0:
 891       # Padding to the end
 892       inputs = array_ops.pad(input_feat,
 893                              array_ops.constant(
 894                                  [0, 0, 0, slice_offset],
 895                                  shape=[2, 2],
 896                                  dtype=dtypes.int32), "CONSTANT")
 897     elif slice_offset < 0:
 898       # Padding to the front
 899       inputs = array_ops.pad(input_feat,
 900                              array_ops.constant(
 901                                  [0, 0, -slice_offset, 0],
 902                                  shape=[2, 2],
 903                                  dtype=dtypes.int32), "CONSTANT")
 904       slice_offset = 0
 905     else:
 906       inputs = input_feat
 907     freq_inputs = []
 908     if not self._start_freqindex_list:
 909       if len(self._num_frequency_blocks) != 1:
 910         raise ValueError("Length of num_frequency_blocks"
 911                          " is not 1, but instead is %d",
 912                          len(self._num_frequency_blocks))
 913       num_feats = int(
 914           (input_size - self._feature_size) / (self._frequency_skip)) + 1
 915       if num_feats != self._num_frequency_blocks[0]:
 916         raise ValueError(
 917             "Invalid num_frequency_blocks, requires %d but gets %d, please"
 918             " check the input size and filter config are correct." %
 919             (self._num_frequency_blocks[0], num_feats))
 920       block_inputs = []
 921       for f in range(num_feats):
 922         cur_input = array_ops.slice(
 923             inputs, [0, slice_offset + f * self._frequency_skip],
 924             [-1, self._feature_size])
 925         block_inputs.append(cur_input)
 926       freq_inputs.append(block_inputs)
 927     else:
 928       if len(self._start_freqindex_list) != len(self._end_freqindex_list):
 929         raise ValueError("Length of start and end freqindex_list"
 930                          " does not match %d %d",
 931                          len(self._start_freqindex_list),
 932                          len(self._end_freqindex_list))
 933       if len(self._num_frequency_blocks) != len(self._start_freqindex_list):
 934         raise ValueError("Length of num_frequency_blocks"
 935                          " is not equal to start_freqindex_list %d %d",
 936                          len(self._num_frequency_blocks),
 937                          len(self._start_freqindex_list))
 938       for b in range(len(self._start_freqindex_list)):
 939         start_index = self._start_freqindex_list[b]
 940         end_index = self._end_freqindex_list[b]
 941         cur_size = end_index - start_index
 942         block_feats = int(
 943             (cur_size - self._feature_size) / (self._frequency_skip)) + 1
 944         if block_feats != self._num_frequency_blocks[b]:
 945           raise ValueError(
 946               "Invalid num_frequency_blocks, requires %d but gets %d, please"
 947               " check the input size and filter config are correct." %
 948               (self._num_frequency_blocks[b], block_feats))
 949         block_inputs = []
 950         for f in range(block_feats):
 951           cur_input = array_ops.slice(
 952               inputs,
 953               [0, start_index + slice_offset + f * self._frequency_skip],
 954               [-1, self._feature_size])
 955           block_inputs.append(cur_input)
 956         freq_inputs.append(block_inputs)
 957     return freq_inputs
 958 
 959 
 960 class BidirectionalGridLSTMCell(GridLSTMCell):
 961   """Bidirectional GridLstm cell.
 962 
 963   The bidirection connection is only used in the frequency direction, which
 964   hence doesn't affect the time direction's real-time processing that is
 965   required for online recognition systems.
 966   The current implementation uses different weights for the two directions.
 967   """
 968 
 969   def __init__(self,
 970                num_units,
 971                use_peepholes=False,
 972                share_time_frequency_weights=False,
 973                cell_clip=None,
 974                initializer=None,
 975                num_unit_shards=1,
 976                forget_bias=1.0,
 977                feature_size=None,
 978                frequency_skip=None,
 979                num_frequency_blocks=None,
 980                start_freqindex_list=None,
 981                end_freqindex_list=None,
 982                couple_input_forget_gates=False,
 983                backward_slice_offset=0,
 984                reuse=None):
 985     """Initialize the parameters for an LSTM cell.
 986 
 987     Args:
 988       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
 989       use_peepholes: (optional) bool, default False. Set True to enable
 990         diagonal/peephole connections.
 991       share_time_frequency_weights: (optional) bool, default False. Set True to
 992         enable shared cell weights between time and frequency LSTMs.
 993       cell_clip: (optional) A float value, default None, if provided the cell
 994         state is clipped by this value prior to the cell output activation.
 995       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
 996         projection matrices, default None.
 997       num_unit_shards: (optional) int, default 1, How to split the weight
 998         matrix. If > 1, the weight matrix is stored across num_unit_shards.
 999       forget_bias: (optional) float, default 1.0, The initial bias of the
1000         forget gates, used to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning
1001         of the training.
1002       feature_size: (optional) int, default None, The size of the input feature
1003         the LSTM spans over.
1004       frequency_skip: (optional) int, default None, The amount the LSTM filter
1005         is shifted by in frequency.
1006       num_frequency_blocks: [required] A list of frequency blocks needed to
1007         cover the whole input feature splitting defined by start_freqindex_list
1008         and end_freqindex_list.
1009       start_freqindex_list: [optional], list of ints, default None,  The
1010         starting frequency index for each frequency block.
1011       end_freqindex_list: [optional], list of ints, default None. The ending
1012         frequency index for each frequency block.
1013       couple_input_forget_gates: (optional) bool, default False, Whether to
1014         couple the input and forget gates, i.e. f_gate = 1.0 - i_gate, to reduce
1015         model parameters and computation cost.
1016       backward_slice_offset: (optional) int32, default 0, the starting offset to
1017         slice the feature for backward processing.
1018       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1019         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1020         the given variables, an error is raised.
1021     """
1022     super(BidirectionalGridLSTMCell, self).__init__(
1023         num_units, use_peepholes, share_time_frequency_weights, cell_clip,
1024         initializer, num_unit_shards, forget_bias, feature_size, frequency_skip,
1025         num_frequency_blocks, start_freqindex_list, end_freqindex_list,
1026         couple_input_forget_gates, True, reuse)
1027     self._backward_slice_offset = int(backward_slice_offset)
1028     state_names = ""
1029     for direction in ["fwd", "bwd"]:
1030       for block_index in range(len(self._num_frequency_blocks)):
1031         for freq_index in range(self._num_frequency_blocks[block_index]):
1032           name_prefix = "%s_state_f%02d_b%02d" % (direction, freq_index,
1033                                                   block_index)
1034           state_names += ("%s_c, %s_m," % (name_prefix, name_prefix))
1035     self._state_tuple_type = collections.namedtuple(
1036         "BidirectionalGridLSTMStateTuple", state_names.strip(","))
1037     self._state_size = self._state_tuple_type(*(
1038         [num_units, num_units] * self._total_blocks * 2))
1039     self._output_size = 2 * num_units * self._total_blocks * 2
1040 
1041   def call(self, inputs, state):
1042     """Run one step of LSTM.
1043 
1044     Args:
1045       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, [batch, num_units].
1046       state: tuple of Tensors, 2D, [batch, state_size].
1047 
1048     Returns:
1049       A tuple containing:
1050       - A 2D, [batch, output_dim], Tensor representing the output of the LSTM
1051         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
1052         Here output_dim is num_units.
1053       - A 2D, [batch, state_size], Tensor representing the new state of LSTM
1054         after reading "inputs" when previous state was "state".
1055     Raises:
1056       ValueError: if an input_size was specified and the provided inputs have
1057         a different dimension.
1058     """
1059     batch_size = inputs.shape[0].value or array_ops.shape(inputs)[0]
1060     fwd_inputs = self._make_tf_features(inputs)
1061     if self._backward_slice_offset:
1062       bwd_inputs = self._make_tf_features(inputs, self._backward_slice_offset)
1063     else:
1064       bwd_inputs = fwd_inputs
1065 
1066     # Forward processing
1067     with vs.variable_scope("fwd"):
1068       fwd_m_out_lst = []
1069       fwd_state_out_lst = []
1070       for block in range(len(fwd_inputs)):
1071         fwd_m_out_lst_current, fwd_state_out_lst_current = self._compute(
1072             fwd_inputs[block],
1073             block,
1074             state,
1075             batch_size,
1076             state_prefix="fwd_state",
1077             state_is_tuple=True)
1078         fwd_m_out_lst.extend(fwd_m_out_lst_current)
1079         fwd_state_out_lst.extend(fwd_state_out_lst_current)
1080     # Backward processing
1081     bwd_m_out_lst = []
1082     bwd_state_out_lst = []
1083     with vs.variable_scope("bwd"):
1084       for block in range(len(bwd_inputs)):
1085         # Reverse the blocks
1086         bwd_inputs_reverse = bwd_inputs[block][::-1]
1087         bwd_m_out_lst_current, bwd_state_out_lst_current = self._compute(
1088             bwd_inputs_reverse,
1089             block,
1090             state,
1091             batch_size,
1092             state_prefix="bwd_state",
1093             state_is_tuple=True)
1094         bwd_m_out_lst.extend(bwd_m_out_lst_current)
1095         bwd_state_out_lst.extend(bwd_state_out_lst_current)
1096     state_out = self._state_tuple_type(*(fwd_state_out_lst + bwd_state_out_lst))
1097     # Outputs are always concated as it is never used separately.
1098     m_out = array_ops.concat(fwd_m_out_lst + bwd_m_out_lst, 1)
1099     return m_out, state_out
1100

1102 # pylint: disable=protected-access
1103 _Linear = core_rnn_cell._Linear  # pylint: disable=invalid-name

1108 class AttentionCellWrapper(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1109   """Basic attention cell wrapper.
1110 
1111   Implementation based on https://arxiv.org/abs/1409.0473.
1112   """
1113 
1114   def __init__(self,
1115                cell,
1116                attn_length,
1117                attn_size=None,
1118                attn_vec_size=None,
1119                input_size=None,
1120                state_is_tuple=True,
1121                reuse=None):
1122     """Create a cell with attention.
1123 
1124     Args:
1125       cell: an RNNCell, an attention is added to it.
1126       attn_length: integer, the size of an attention window.
1127       attn_size: integer, the size of an attention vector. Equal to
1128           cell.output_size by default.
1129       attn_vec_size: integer, the number of convolutional features calculated
1130           on attention state and a size of the hidden layer built from
1131           base cell state. Equal attn_size to by default.
1132       input_size: integer, the size of a hidden linear layer,
1133           built from inputs and attention. Derived from the input tensor
1134           by default.
1135       state_is_tuple: If True, accepted and returned states are n-tuples, where
1136         `n = len(cells)`.  By default (False), the states are all
1137         concatenated along the column axis.
1138       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1139         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1140         the given variables, an error is raised.
1141 
1142     Raises:
1143       TypeError: if cell is not an RNNCell.
1144       ValueError: if cell returns a state tuple but the flag
1145           `state_is_tuple` is `False` or if attn_length is zero or less.
1146     """
1147     super(AttentionCellWrapper, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1148     rnn_cell_impl.assert_like_rnncell("cell", cell)
1149     if nest.is_sequence(cell.state_size) and not state_is_tuple:
1150       raise ValueError(
1151           "Cell returns tuple of states, but the flag "
1152           "state_is_tuple is not set. State size is: %s" % str(cell.state_size))
1153     if attn_length <= 0:
1154       raise ValueError(
1155           "attn_length should be greater than zero, got %s" % str(attn_length))
1156     if not state_is_tuple:
1157       logging.warn("%s: Using a concatenated state is slower and will soon be "
1158                    "deprecated.  Use state_is_tuple=True.", self)
1159     if attn_size is None:
1160       attn_size = cell.output_size
1161     if attn_vec_size is None:
1162       attn_vec_size = attn_size
1163     self._state_is_tuple = state_is_tuple
1164     self._cell = cell
1165     self._attn_vec_size = attn_vec_size
1166     self._input_size = input_size
1167     self._attn_size = attn_size
1168     self._attn_length = attn_length
1169     self._reuse = reuse
1170     self._linear1 = None
1171     self._linear2 = None
1172     self._linear3 = None
1173 
1174   @property
1175   def state_size(self):
1176     size = (self._cell.state_size, self._attn_size,
1177             self._attn_size * self._attn_length)
1178     if self._state_is_tuple:
1179       return size
1180     else:
1181       return sum(list(size))
1182 
1183   @property
1184   def output_size(self):
1185     return self._attn_size
1186 
1187   def call(self, inputs, state):
1188     """Long short-term memory cell with attention (LSTMA)."""
1189     if self._state_is_tuple:
1190       state, attns, attn_states = state
1191     else:
1192       states = state
1193       state = array_ops.slice(states, [0, 0], [-1, self._cell.state_size])
1194       attns = array_ops.slice(states, [0, self._cell.state_size],
1195                               [-1, self._attn_size])
1196       attn_states = array_ops.slice(
1197           states, [0, self._cell.state_size + self._attn_size],
1198           [-1, self._attn_size * self._attn_length])
1199     attn_states = array_ops.reshape(attn_states,
1200                                     [-1, self._attn_length, self._attn_size])
1201     input_size = self._input_size
1202     if input_size is None:
1203       input_size = inputs.get_shape().as_list()[1]
1204     if self._linear1 is None:
1205       self._linear1 = _Linear([inputs, attns], input_size, True)
1206     inputs = self._linear1([inputs, attns])
1207     cell_output, new_state = self._cell(inputs, state)
1208     if self._state_is_tuple:
1209       new_state_cat = array_ops.concat(nest.flatten(new_state), 1)
1210     else:
1211       new_state_cat = new_state
1212     new_attns, new_attn_states = self._attention(new_state_cat, attn_states)
1213     with vs.variable_scope("attn_output_projection"):
1214       if self._linear2 is None:
1215         self._linear2 = _Linear([cell_output, new_attns], self._attn_size, True)
1216       output = self._linear2([cell_output, new_attns])
1217     new_attn_states = array_ops.concat(
1218         [new_attn_states, array_ops.expand_dims(output, 1)], 1)
1219     new_attn_states = array_ops.reshape(
1220         new_attn_states, [-1, self._attn_length * self._attn_size])
1221     new_state = (new_state, new_attns, new_attn_states)
1222     if not self._state_is_tuple:
1223       new_state = array_ops.concat(list(new_state), 1)
1224     return output, new_state
1225 
1226   def _attention(self, query, attn_states):
1227     conv2d = nn_ops.conv2d
1228     reduce_sum = math_ops.reduce_sum
1229     softmax = nn_ops.softmax
1230     tanh = math_ops.tanh
1231 
1232     with vs.variable_scope("attention"):
1233       k = vs.get_variable("attn_w",
1234                           [1, 1, self._attn_size, self._attn_vec_size])
1235       v = vs.get_variable("attn_v", [self._attn_vec_size])
1236       hidden = array_ops.reshape(attn_states,
1237                                  [-1, self._attn_length, 1, self._attn_size])
1238       hidden_features = conv2d(hidden, k, [1, 1, 1, 1], "SAME")
1239       if self._linear3 is None:
1240         self._linear3 = _Linear(query, self._attn_vec_size, True)
1241       y = self._linear3(query)
1242       y = array_ops.reshape(y, [-1, 1, 1, self._attn_vec_size])
1243       s = reduce_sum(v * tanh(hidden_features + y), [2, 3])
1244       a = softmax(s)
1245       d = reduce_sum(
1246           array_ops.reshape(a, [-1, self._attn_length, 1, 1]) * hidden, [1, 2])
1247       new_attns = array_ops.reshape(d, [-1, self._attn_size])
1248       new_attn_states = array_ops.slice(attn_states, [0, 1, 0], [-1, -1, -1])
1249       return new_attns, new_attn_states
1250 
1251 
1252 class HighwayWrapper(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1253   """RNNCell wrapper that adds highway connection on cell input and output.
1254 
1255   Based on:
1256     R. K. Srivastava, K. Greff, and J. Schmidhuber, "Highway networks",
1257     arXiv preprint arXiv:1505.00387, 2015.
1258     https://arxiv.org/abs/1505.00387
1259   """
1260 
1261   def __init__(self,
1262                cell,
1263                couple_carry_transform_gates=True,
1264                carry_bias_init=1.0):
1265     """Constructs a `HighwayWrapper` for `cell`.
1266 
1267     Args:
1268       cell: An instance of `RNNCell`.
1269       couple_carry_transform_gates: boolean, should the Carry and Transform gate
1270         be coupled.
1271       carry_bias_init: float, carry gates bias initialization.
1272     """
1273     self._cell = cell
1274     self._couple_carry_transform_gates = couple_carry_transform_gates
1275     self._carry_bias_init = carry_bias_init
1276 
1277   @property
1278   def state_size(self):
1279     return self._cell.state_size
1280 
1281   @property
1282   def output_size(self):
1283     return self._cell.output_size
1284 
1285   def zero_state(self, batch_size, dtype):
1286     with ops.name_scope(type(self).__name__ + "ZeroState", values=[batch_size]):
1287       return self._cell.zero_state(batch_size, dtype)
1288 
1289   def _highway(self, inp, out):
1290     input_size = inp.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1].value
1291     carry_weight = vs.get_variable("carry_w", [input_size, input_size])
1292     carry_bias = vs.get_variable(
1293         "carry_b", [input_size],
1294         initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(self._carry_bias_init))
1295     carry = math_ops.sigmoid(nn_ops.xw_plus_b(inp, carry_weight, carry_bias))
1296     if self._couple_carry_transform_gates:
1297       transform = 1 - carry
1298     else:
1299       transform_weight = vs.get_variable("transform_w",
1300                                          [input_size, input_size])
1301       transform_bias = vs.get_variable(
1302           "transform_b", [input_size],
1303           initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(-self._carry_bias_init))
1304       transform = math_ops.sigmoid(
1305           nn_ops.xw_plus_b(inp, transform_weight, transform_bias))
1306     return inp * carry + out * transform
1307 
1308   def __call__(self, inputs, state, scope=None):
1309     """Run the cell and add its inputs to its outputs.
1310 
1311     Args:
1312       inputs: cell inputs.
1313       state: cell state.
1314       scope: optional cell scope.
1315 
1316     Returns:
1317       Tuple of cell outputs and new state.
1318 
1319     Raises:
1320       TypeError: If cell inputs and outputs have different structure (type).
1321       ValueError: If cell inputs and outputs have different structure (value).
1322     """
1323     outputs, new_state = self._cell(inputs, state, scope=scope)
1324     nest.assert_same_structure(inputs, outputs)
1325 
1326     # Ensure shapes match
1327     def assert_shape_match(inp, out):
1328       inp.get_shape().assert_is_compatible_with(out.get_shape())
1329 
1330     nest.map_structure(assert_shape_match, inputs, outputs)
1331     res_outputs = nest.map_structure(self._highway, inputs, outputs)
1332     return (res_outputs, new_state)
1333

1335 class LayerNormBasicLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1336   """LSTM unit with layer normalization and recurrent dropout.
1337 
1338   This class adds layer normalization and recurrent dropout to a
1339   basic LSTM unit. Layer normalization implementation is based on:
1340 
1341     https://arxiv.org/abs/1607.06450.
1342 
1343   "Layer Normalization"
1344   Jimmy Lei Ba, Jamie Ryan Kiros, Geoffrey E. Hinton
1345 
1346   and is applied before the internal nonlinearities.
1347   Recurrent dropout is base on:
1348 
1349     https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.05118
1350 
1351   "Recurrent Dropout without Memory Loss"
1352   Stanislau Semeniuta, Aliaksei Severyn, Erhardt Barth.
1353   """
1354 
1355   def __init__(self,
1356                num_units,
1357                forget_bias=1.0,
1358                input_size=None,
1359                activation=math_ops.tanh,
1360                layer_norm=True,
1361                norm_gain=1.0,
1362                norm_shift=0.0,
1363                dropout_keep_prob=1.0,
1364                dropout_prob_seed=None,
1365                reuse=None):
1366     """Initializes the basic LSTM cell.
1367 
1368     Args:
1369       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell.
1370       forget_bias: float, The bias added to forget gates (see above).
1371       input_size: Deprecated and unused.
1372       activation: Activation function of the inner states.
1373       layer_norm: If `True`, layer normalization will be applied.
1374       norm_gain: float, The layer normalization gain initial value. If
1375         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
1376       norm_shift: float, The layer normalization shift initial value. If
1377         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
1378       dropout_keep_prob: unit Tensor or float between 0 and 1 representing the
1379         recurrent dropout probability value. If float and 1.0, no dropout will
1380         be applied.
1381       dropout_prob_seed: (optional) integer, the randomness seed.
1382       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1383         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1384         the given variables, an error is raised.
1385     """
1386     super(LayerNormBasicLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1387 
1388     if input_size is not None:
1389       logging.warn("%s: The input_size parameter is deprecated.", self)
1390 
1391     self._num_units = num_units
1392     self._activation = activation
1393     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
1394     self._keep_prob = dropout_keep_prob
1395     self._seed = dropout_prob_seed
1396     self._layer_norm = layer_norm
1397     self._norm_gain = norm_gain
1398     self._norm_shift = norm_shift
1399     self._reuse = reuse
1400 
1401   @property
1402   def state_size(self):
1403     return rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(self._num_units, self._num_units)
1404 
1405   @property
1406   def output_size(self):
1407     return self._num_units
1408 
1409   def _norm(self, inp, scope, dtype=dtypes.float32):
1410     shape = inp.get_shape()[-1:]
1411     gamma_init = init_ops.constant_initializer(self._norm_gain)
1412     beta_init = init_ops.constant_initializer(self._norm_shift)
1413     with vs.variable_scope(scope):
1414       # Initialize beta and gamma for use by layer_norm.
1415       vs.get_variable("gamma", shape=shape, initializer=gamma_init, dtype=dtype)
1416       vs.get_variable("beta", shape=shape, initializer=beta_init, dtype=dtype)
1417     normalized = layers.layer_norm(inp, reuse=True, scope=scope)
1418     return normalized
1419 
1420   def _linear(self, args):
1421     out_size = 4 * self._num_units
1422     proj_size = args.get_shape()[-1]
1423     dtype = args.dtype
1424     weights = vs.get_variable("kernel", [proj_size, out_size], dtype=dtype)
1425     out = math_ops.matmul(args, weights)
1426     if not self._layer_norm:
1427       bias = vs.get_variable("bias", [out_size], dtype=dtype)
1428       out = nn_ops.bias_add(out, bias)
1429     return out
1430 
1431   def call(self, inputs, state):
1432     """LSTM cell with layer normalization and recurrent dropout."""
1433     c, h = state
1434     args = array_ops.concat([inputs, h], 1)
1435     concat = self._linear(args)
1436     dtype = args.dtype
1437 
1438     i, j, f, o = array_ops.split(value=concat, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
1439     if self._layer_norm:
1440       i = self._norm(i, "input", dtype=dtype)
1441       j = self._norm(j, "transform", dtype=dtype)
1442       f = self._norm(f, "forget", dtype=dtype)
1443       o = self._norm(o, "output", dtype=dtype)
1444 
1445     g = self._activation(j)
1446     if (not isinstance(self._keep_prob, float)) or self._keep_prob < 1:
1447       g = nn_ops.dropout(g, self._keep_prob, seed=self._seed)
1448 
1449     new_c = (
1450         c * math_ops.sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias) + math_ops.sigmoid(i) * g)
1451     if self._layer_norm:
1452       new_c = self._norm(new_c, "state", dtype=dtype)
1453     new_h = self._activation(new_c) * math_ops.sigmoid(o)
1454 
1455     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_c, new_h)
1456     return new_h, new_state
1457 
1458 
1459 class NASCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1460   """Neural Architecture Search (NAS) recurrent network cell.
1461 
1462   This implements the recurrent cell from the paper:
1463 
1464     https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.01578
1465 
1466   Barret Zoph and Quoc V. Le.
1467   "Neural Architecture Search with Reinforcement Learning" Proc. ICLR 2017.
1468 
1469   The class uses an optional projection layer.
1470   """
1471 
1472   def __init__(self, num_units, num_proj=None, use_biases=False, reuse=None):
1473     """Initialize the parameters for a NAS cell.
1474 
1475     Args:
1476       num_units: int, The number of units in the NAS cell
1477       num_proj: (optional) int, The output dimensionality for the projection
1478         matrices.  If None, no projection is performed.
1479       use_biases: (optional) bool, If True then use biases within the cell. This
1480         is False by default.
1481       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1482         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1483         the given variables, an error is raised.
1484     """
1485     super(NASCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1486     self._num_units = num_units
1487     self._num_proj = num_proj
1488     self._use_biases = use_biases
1489     self._reuse = reuse
1490 
1491     if num_proj is not None:
1492       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_proj)
1493       self._output_size = num_proj
1494     else:
1495       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_units)
1496       self._output_size = num_units
1497 
1498   @property
1499   def state_size(self):
1500     return self._state_size
1501 
1502   @property
1503   def output_size(self):
1504     return self._output_size
1505 
1506   def call(self, inputs, state):
1507     """Run one step of NAS Cell.
1508 
1509     Args:
1510       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
1511       state: This must be a tuple of state Tensors, both `2-D`, with column
1512         sizes `c_state` and `m_state`.
1513 
1514     Returns:
1515       A tuple containing:
1516       - A `2-D, [batch x output_dim]`, Tensor representing the output of the
1517         NAS Cell after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
1518         Here output_dim is:
1519            num_proj if num_proj was set,
1520            num_units otherwise.
1521       - Tensor(s) representing the new state of NAS Cell after reading `inputs`
1522         when the previous state was `state`.  Same type and shape(s) as `state`.
1523 
1524     Raises:
1525       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
1526         static shape inference.
1527     """
1528     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
1529     tanh = math_ops.tanh
1530     relu = nn_ops.relu
1531 
1532     num_proj = self._num_units if self._num_proj is None else self._num_proj
1533 
1534     (c_prev, m_prev) = state
1535 
1536     dtype = inputs.dtype
1537     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
1538     if input_size.value is None:
1539       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
1540     # Variables for the NAS cell. W_m is all matrices multiplying the
1541     # hiddenstate and W_inputs is all matrices multiplying the inputs.
1542     concat_w_m = vs.get_variable("recurrent_kernel",
1543                                  [num_proj, 8 * self._num_units], dtype)
1544     concat_w_inputs = vs.get_variable(
1545         "kernel", [input_size.value, 8 * self._num_units], dtype)
1546 
1547     m_matrix = math_ops.matmul(m_prev, concat_w_m)
1548     inputs_matrix = math_ops.matmul(inputs, concat_w_inputs)
1549 
1550     if self._use_biases:
1551       b = vs.get_variable(
1552           "bias",
1553           shape=[8 * self._num_units],
1554           initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
1555           dtype=dtype)
1556       m_matrix = nn_ops.bias_add(m_matrix, b)
1557 
1558     # The NAS cell branches into 8 different splits for both the hiddenstate
1559     # and the input
1560     m_matrix_splits = array_ops.split(
1561         axis=1, num_or_size_splits=8, value=m_matrix)
1562     inputs_matrix_splits = array_ops.split(
1563         axis=1, num_or_size_splits=8, value=inputs_matrix)
1564 
1565     # First layer
1566     layer1_0 = sigmoid(inputs_matrix_splits[0] + m_matrix_splits[0])
1567     layer1_1 = relu(inputs_matrix_splits[1] + m_matrix_splits[1])
1568     layer1_2 = sigmoid(inputs_matrix_splits[2] + m_matrix_splits[2])
1569     layer1_3 = relu(inputs_matrix_splits[3] * m_matrix_splits[3])
1570     layer1_4 = tanh(inputs_matrix_splits[4] + m_matrix_splits[4])
1571     layer1_5 = sigmoid(inputs_matrix_splits[5] + m_matrix_splits[5])
1572     layer1_6 = tanh(inputs_matrix_splits[6] + m_matrix_splits[6])
1573     layer1_7 = sigmoid(inputs_matrix_splits[7] + m_matrix_splits[7])
1574 
1575     # Second layer
1576     l2_0 = tanh(layer1_0 * layer1_1)
1577     l2_1 = tanh(layer1_2 + layer1_3)
1578     l2_2 = tanh(layer1_4 * layer1_5)
1579     l2_3 = sigmoid(layer1_6 + layer1_7)
1580 
1581     # Inject the cell
1582     l2_0 = tanh(l2_0 + c_prev)
1583 
1584     # Third layer
1585     l3_0_pre = l2_0 * l2_1
1586     new_c = l3_0_pre  # create new cell
1587     l3_0 = l3_0_pre
1588     l3_1 = tanh(l2_2 + l2_3)
1589 
1590     # Final layer
1591     new_m = tanh(l3_0 * l3_1)
1592 
1593     # Projection layer if specified
1594     if self._num_proj is not None:
1595       concat_w_proj = vs.get_variable("projection_weights",
1596                                       [self._num_units, self._num_proj], dtype)
1597       new_m = math_ops.matmul(new_m, concat_w_proj)
1598 
1599     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_c, new_m)
1600     return new_m, new_state
1601 
1602 
1603 class UGRNNCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1604   """Update Gate Recurrent Neural Network (UGRNN) cell.
1605 
1606   Compromise between a LSTM/GRU and a vanilla RNN.  There is only one
1607   gate, and that is to determine whether the unit should be
1608   integrating or computing instantaneously.  This is the recurrent
1609   idea of the feedforward Highway Network.
1610 
1611   This implements the recurrent cell from the paper:
1612 
1613     https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.09913
1614 
1615   Jasmine Collins, Jascha Sohl-Dickstein, and David Sussillo.
1616   "Capacity and Trainability in Recurrent Neural Networks" Proc. ICLR 2017.
1617   """
1618 
1619   def __init__(self,
1620                num_units,
1621                initializer=None,
1622                forget_bias=1.0,
1623                activation=math_ops.tanh,
1624                reuse=None):
1625     """Initialize the parameters for an UGRNN cell.
1626 
1627     Args:
1628       num_units: int, The number of units in the UGRNN cell
1629       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight matrices.
1630       forget_bias: (optional) float, default 1.0, The initial bias of the
1631         forget gate, used to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning
1632         of the training.
1633       activation: (optional) Activation function of the inner states.
1634         Default is `tf.tanh`.
1635       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1636         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1637         the given variables, an error is raised.
1638     """
1639     super(UGRNNCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1640     self._num_units = num_units
1641     self._initializer = initializer
1642     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
1643     self._activation = activation
1644     self._reuse = reuse
1645     self._linear = None
1646 
1647   @property
1648   def state_size(self):
1649     return self._num_units
1650 
1651   @property
1652   def output_size(self):
1653     return self._num_units
1654 
1655   def call(self, inputs, state):
1656     """Run one step of UGRNN.
1657 
1658     Args:
1659       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x input size.
1660       state: state Tensor, 2D, batch x num units.
1661 
1662     Returns:
1663       new_output: batch x num units, Tensor representing the output of the UGRNN
1664         after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`. Identical to
1665         `new_state`.
1666       new_state: batch x num units, Tensor representing the state of the UGRNN
1667         after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
1668 
1669     Raises:
1670       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
1671         static shape inference.
1672     """
1673     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
1674 
1675     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
1676     if input_size.value is None:
1677       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
1678 
1679     with vs.variable_scope(
1680         vs.get_variable_scope(), initializer=self._initializer):
1681       cell_inputs = array_ops.concat([inputs, state], 1)
1682       if self._linear is None:
1683         self._linear = _Linear(cell_inputs, 2 * self._num_units, True)
1684       rnn_matrix = self._linear(cell_inputs)
1685 
1686       [g_act, c_act] = array_ops.split(
1687           axis=1, num_or_size_splits=2, value=rnn_matrix)
1688 
1689       c = self._activation(c_act)
1690       g = sigmoid(g_act + self._forget_bias)
1691       new_state = g * state + (1.0 - g) * c
1692       new_output = new_state
1693 
1694     return new_output, new_state
1695 
1696 
1697 class IntersectionRNNCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1698   """Intersection Recurrent Neural Network (+RNN) cell.
1699 
1700   Architecture with coupled recurrent gate as well as coupled depth
1701   gate, designed to improve information flow through stacked RNNs. As the
1702   architecture uses depth gating, the dimensionality of the depth
1703   output (y) also should not change through depth (input size == output size).
1704   To achieve this, the first layer of a stacked Intersection RNN projects
1705   the inputs to N (num units) dimensions. Therefore when initializing an
1706   IntersectionRNNCell, one should set `num_in_proj = N` for the first layer
1707   and use default settings for subsequent layers.
1708 
1709   This implements the recurrent cell from the paper:
1710 
1711     https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.09913
1712 
1713   Jasmine Collins, Jascha Sohl-Dickstein, and David Sussillo.
1714   "Capacity and Trainability in Recurrent Neural Networks" Proc. ICLR 2017.
1715 
1716   The Intersection RNN is built for use in deeply stacked
1717   RNNs so it may not achieve best performance with depth 1.
1718   """
1719 
1720   def __init__(self,
1721                num_units,
1722                num_in_proj=None,
1723                initializer=None,
1724                forget_bias=1.0,
1725                y_activation=nn_ops.relu,
1726                reuse=None):
1727     """Initialize the parameters for an +RNN cell.
1728 
1729     Args:
1730       num_units: int, The number of units in the +RNN cell
1731       num_in_proj: (optional) int, The input dimensionality for the RNN.
1732         If creating the first layer of an +RNN, this should be set to
1733         `num_units`. Otherwise, this should be set to `None` (default).
1734         If `None`, dimensionality of `inputs` should be equal to `num_units`,
1735         otherwise ValueError is thrown.
1736       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight matrices.
1737       forget_bias: (optional) float, default 1.0, The initial bias of the
1738         forget gates, used to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning
1739         of the training.
1740       y_activation: (optional) Activation function of the states passed
1741         through depth. Default is 'tf.nn.relu`.
1742       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1743         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1744         the given variables, an error is raised.
1745     """
1746     super(IntersectionRNNCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1747     self._num_units = num_units
1748     self._initializer = initializer
1749     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
1750     self._num_input_proj = num_in_proj
1751     self._y_activation = y_activation
1752     self._reuse = reuse
1753     self._linear1 = None
1754     self._linear2 = None
1755 
1756   @property
1757   def state_size(self):
1758     return self._num_units
1759 
1760   @property
1761   def output_size(self):
1762     return self._num_units
1763 
1764   def call(self, inputs, state):
1765     """Run one step of the Intersection RNN.
1766 
1767     Args:
1768       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x input size.
1769       state: state Tensor, 2D, batch x num units.
1770 
1771     Returns:
1772       new_y: batch x num units, Tensor representing the output of the +RNN
1773         after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
1774       new_state: batch x num units, Tensor representing the state of the +RNN
1775         after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
1776 
1777     Raises:
1778       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from `inputs` via
1779         static shape inference.
1780       ValueError: If input size != output size (these must be equal when
1781         using the Intersection RNN).
1782     """
1783     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
1784     tanh = math_ops.tanh
1785 
1786     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
1787     if input_size.value is None:
1788       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
1789 
1790     with vs.variable_scope(
1791         vs.get_variable_scope(), initializer=self._initializer):
1792       # read-in projections (should be used for first layer in deep +RNN
1793       # to transform size of inputs from I --> N)
1794       if input_size.value != self._num_units:
1795         if self._num_input_proj:
1796           with vs.variable_scope("in_projection"):
1797             if self._linear1 is None:
1798               self._linear1 = _Linear(inputs, self._num_units, True)
1799             inputs = self._linear1(inputs)
1800         else:
1801           raise ValueError("Must have input size == output size for "
1802                            "Intersection RNN. To fix, num_in_proj should "
1803                            "be set to num_units at cell init.")
1804 
1805       n_dim = i_dim = self._num_units
1806       cell_inputs = array_ops.concat([inputs, state], 1)
1807       if self._linear2 is None:
1808         self._linear2 = _Linear(cell_inputs, 2 * n_dim + 2 * i_dim, True)
1809       rnn_matrix = self._linear2(cell_inputs)
1810 
1811       gh_act = rnn_matrix[:, :n_dim]  # b x n
1812       h_act = rnn_matrix[:, n_dim:2 * n_dim]  # b x n
1813       gy_act = rnn_matrix[:, 2 * n_dim:2 * n_dim + i_dim]  # b x i
1814       y_act = rnn_matrix[:, 2 * n_dim + i_dim:2 * n_dim + 2 * i_dim]  # b x i
1815 
1816       h = tanh(h_act)
1817       y = self._y_activation(y_act)
1818       gh = sigmoid(gh_act + self._forget_bias)
1819       gy = sigmoid(gy_act + self._forget_bias)
1820 
1821       new_state = gh * state + (1.0 - gh) * h  # passed thru time
1822       new_y = gy * inputs + (1.0 - gy) * y  # passed thru depth
1823 
1824     return new_y, new_state
1825

1827 _REGISTERED_OPS = None
