1830 class CompiledWrapper(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1831   """Wraps step execution in an XLA JIT scope."""
1832 
1833   def __init__(self, cell, compile_stateful=False):
1834     """Create CompiledWrapper cell.
1835 
1836     Args:
1837       cell: Instance of `RNNCell`.
1838       compile_stateful: Whether to compile stateful ops like initializers
1839         and random number generators (default: False).
1840     """
1841     self._cell = cell
1842     self._compile_stateful = compile_stateful
1843 
1844   @property
1845   def state_size(self):
1846     return self._cell.state_size
1847 
1848   @property
1849   def output_size(self):
1850     return self._cell.output_size
1851 
1852   def zero_state(self, batch_size, dtype):
1853     with ops.name_scope(type(self).__name__ + "ZeroState", values=[batch_size]):
1854       return self._cell.zero_state(batch_size, dtype)
1855 
1856   def __call__(self, inputs, state, scope=None):
1857     if self._compile_stateful:
1858       compile_ops = True
1859     else:
1860 
1861       def compile_ops(node_def):
1862         global _REGISTERED_OPS
1863         if _REGISTERED_OPS is None:
1864           _REGISTERED_OPS = op_def_registry.get_registered_ops()
1865         return not _REGISTERED_OPS[node_def.op].is_stateful
1866 
1867     with jit.experimental_jit_scope(compile_ops=compile_ops):
1868       return self._cell(inputs, state, scope=scope)
1869 
1870 
1871 def _random_exp_initializer(minval, maxval, seed=None, dtype=dtypes.float32):
1872   """Returns an exponential distribution initializer.
1873 
1874   Args:
1875     minval: float or a scalar float Tensor. With value > 0. Lower bound of the
1876         range of random values to generate.
1877     maxval: float or a scalar float Tensor. With value > minval. Upper bound of
1878         the range of random values to generate.
1879     seed: An integer. Used to create random seeds.
1880     dtype: The data type.
1881 
1882   Returns:
1883     An initializer that generates tensors with an exponential distribution.
1884   """
1885 
1886   def _initializer(shape, dtype=dtype, partition_info=None):
1887     del partition_info  # Unused.
1888     return math_ops.exp(
1889         random_ops.random_uniform(
1890             shape, math_ops.log(minval), math_ops.log(maxval), dtype,
1891             seed=seed))
1892 
1893   return _initializer

1896 class PhasedLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
1897   """Phased LSTM recurrent network cell.
1898 
1899   https://arxiv.org/pdf/1610.09513v1.pdf
1900   """
1901 
1902   def __init__(self,
1903                num_units,
1904                use_peepholes=False,
1905                leak=0.001,
1906                ratio_on=0.1,
1907                trainable_ratio_on=True,
1908                period_init_min=1.0,
1909                period_init_max=1000.0,
1910                reuse=None):
1911     """Initialize the Phased LSTM cell.
1912 
1913     Args:
1914       num_units: int, The number of units in the Phased LSTM cell.
1915       use_peepholes: bool, set True to enable peephole connections.
1916       leak: float or scalar float Tensor with value in [0, 1]. Leak applied
1917           during training.
1918       ratio_on: float or scalar float Tensor with value in [0, 1]. Ratio of the
1919           period during which the gates are open.
1920       trainable_ratio_on: bool, weather ratio_on is trainable.
1921       period_init_min: float or scalar float Tensor. With value > 0.
1922           Minimum value of the initialized period.
1923           The period values are initialized by drawing from the distribution:
1924           e^U(log(period_init_min), log(period_init_max))
1925           Where U(.,.) is the uniform distribution.
1926       period_init_max: float or scalar float Tensor.
1927           With value > period_init_min. Maximum value of the initialized period.
1928       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
1929         in an existing scope. If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
1930         the given variables, an error is raised.
1931     """
1932     super(PhasedLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
1933     self._num_units = num_units
1934     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
1935     self._leak = leak
1936     self._ratio_on = ratio_on
1937     self._trainable_ratio_on = trainable_ratio_on
1938     self._period_init_min = period_init_min
1939     self._period_init_max = period_init_max
1940     self._reuse = reuse
1941     self._linear1 = None
1942     self._linear2 = None
1943     self._linear3 = None
1944 
1945   @property
1946   def state_size(self):
1947     return rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(self._num_units, self._num_units)
1948 
1949   @property
1950   def output_size(self):
1951     return self._num_units
1952 
1953   def _mod(self, x, y):
1954     """Modulo function that propagates x gradients."""
1955     return array_ops.stop_gradient(math_ops.mod(x, y) - x) + x
1956 
1957   def _get_cycle_ratio(self, time, phase, period):
1958     """Compute the cycle ratio in the dtype of the time."""
1959     phase_casted = math_ops.cast(phase, dtype=time.dtype)
1960     period_casted = math_ops.cast(period, dtype=time.dtype)
1961     shifted_time = time - phase_casted
1962     cycle_ratio = self._mod(shifted_time, period_casted) / period_casted
1963     return math_ops.cast(cycle_ratio, dtype=dtypes.float32)
1964 
1965   def call(self, inputs, state):
1966     """Phased LSTM Cell.
1967 
1968     Args:
1969       inputs: A tuple of 2 Tensor.
1970          The first Tensor has shape [batch, 1], and type float32 or float64.
1971          It stores the time.
1972          The second Tensor has shape [batch, features_size], and type float32.
1973          It stores the features.
1974       state: rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple, state from previous timestep.
1975 
1976     Returns:
1977       A tuple containing:
1978       - A Tensor of float32, and shape [batch_size, num_units], representing the
1979         output of the cell.
1980       - A rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple, containing 2 Tensors of float32, shape
1981         [batch_size, num_units], representing the new state and the output.
1982     """
1983     (c_prev, h_prev) = state
1984     (time, x) = inputs
1985 
1986     in_mask_gates = [x, h_prev]
1987     if self._use_peepholes:
1988       in_mask_gates.append(c_prev)
1989 
1990     with vs.variable_scope("mask_gates"):
1991       if self._linear1 is None:
1992         self._linear1 = _Linear(in_mask_gates, 2 * self._num_units, True)
1993 
1994       mask_gates = math_ops.sigmoid(self._linear1(in_mask_gates))
1995       [input_gate, forget_gate] = array_ops.split(
1996           axis=1, num_or_size_splits=2, value=mask_gates)
1997 
1998     with vs.variable_scope("new_input"):
1999       if self._linear2 is None:
2000         self._linear2 = _Linear([x, h_prev], self._num_units, True)
2001       new_input = math_ops.tanh(self._linear2([x, h_prev]))
2002 
2003     new_c = (c_prev * forget_gate + input_gate * new_input)
2004 
2005     in_out_gate = [x, h_prev]
2006     if self._use_peepholes:
2007       in_out_gate.append(new_c)
2008 
2009     with vs.variable_scope("output_gate"):
2010       if self._linear3 is None:
2011         self._linear3 = _Linear(in_out_gate, self._num_units, True)
2012       output_gate = math_ops.sigmoid(self._linear3(in_out_gate))
2013 
2014     new_h = math_ops.tanh(new_c) * output_gate
2015 
2016     period = vs.get_variable(
2017         "period", [self._num_units],
2018         initializer=_random_exp_initializer(self._period_init_min,
2019                                             self._period_init_max))
2020     phase = vs.get_variable(
2021         "phase", [self._num_units],
2022         initializer=init_ops.random_uniform_initializer(0.,
2023                                                         period.initial_value))
2024     ratio_on = vs.get_variable(
2025         "ratio_on", [self._num_units],
2026         initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(self._ratio_on),
2027         trainable=self._trainable_ratio_on)
2028 
2029     cycle_ratio = self._get_cycle_ratio(time, phase, period)
2030 
2031     k_up = 2 * cycle_ratio / ratio_on
2032     k_down = 2 - k_up
2033     k_closed = self._leak * cycle_ratio
2034 
2035     k = array_ops.where(cycle_ratio < ratio_on, k_down, k_closed)
2036     k = array_ops.where(cycle_ratio < 0.5 * ratio_on, k_up, k)
2037 
2038     new_c = k * new_c + (1 - k) * c_prev
2039     new_h = k * new_h + (1 - k) * h_prev
2040 
2041     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_c, new_h)
2042 
2043     return new_h, new_state
2044 
2045 
2046 class ConvLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
2047   """Convolutional LSTM recurrent network cell.
2048 
2049   https://arxiv.org/pdf/1506.04214v1.pdf
2050   """
2051 
2052   def __init__(self,
2053                conv_ndims,
2054                input_shape,
2055                output_channels,
2056                kernel_shape,
2057                use_bias=True,
2058                skip_connection=False,
2059                forget_bias=1.0,
2060                initializers=None,
2061                name="conv_lstm_cell"):
2062     """Construct ConvLSTMCell.
2063 
2064     Args:
2065       conv_ndims: Convolution dimensionality (1, 2 or 3).
2066       input_shape: Shape of the input as int tuple, excluding the batch size.
2067       output_channels: int, number of output channels of the conv LSTM.
2068       kernel_shape: Shape of kernel as in tuple (of size 1,2 or 3).
2069       use_bias: (bool) Use bias in convolutions.
2070       skip_connection: If set to `True`, concatenate the input to the
2071         output of the conv LSTM. Default: `False`.
2072       forget_bias: Forget bias.
2073       initializers: Unused.
2074       name: Name of the module.
2075 
2076     Raises:
2077       ValueError: If `skip_connection` is `True` and stride is different from 1
2078         or if `input_shape` is incompatible with `conv_ndims`.
2079     """
2080     super(ConvLSTMCell, self).__init__(name=name)
2081 
2082     if conv_ndims != len(input_shape) - 1:
2083       raise ValueError("Invalid input_shape {} for conv_ndims={}.".format(
2084           input_shape, conv_ndims))
2085 
2086     self._conv_ndims = conv_ndims
2087     self._input_shape = input_shape
2088     self._output_channels = output_channels
2089     self._kernel_shape = kernel_shape
2090     self._use_bias = use_bias
2091     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
2092     self._skip_connection = skip_connection
2093 
2094     self._total_output_channels = output_channels
2095     if self._skip_connection:
2096       self._total_output_channels += self._input_shape[-1]
2097 
2098     state_size = tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2099         self._input_shape[:-1] + [self._output_channels])
2100     self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(state_size, state_size)
2101     self._output_size = tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2102         self._input_shape[:-1] + [self._total_output_channels])
2103 
2104   @property
2105   def output_size(self):
2106     return self._output_size
2107 
2108   @property
2109   def state_size(self):
2110     return self._state_size
2111 
2112   def call(self, inputs, state, scope=None):
2113     cell, hidden = state
2114     new_hidden = _conv([inputs, hidden], self._kernel_shape,
2115                        4 * self._output_channels, self._use_bias)
2116     gates = array_ops.split(
2117         value=new_hidden, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=self._conv_ndims + 1)
2118 
2119     input_gate, new_input, forget_gate, output_gate = gates
2120     new_cell = math_ops.sigmoid(forget_gate + self._forget_bias) * cell
2121     new_cell += math_ops.sigmoid(input_gate) * math_ops.tanh(new_input)
2122     output = math_ops.tanh(new_cell) * math_ops.sigmoid(output_gate)
2123 
2124     if self._skip_connection:
2125       output = array_ops.concat([output, inputs], axis=-1)
2126     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_cell, output)
2127     return output, new_state
2128

2161 
2162 
2163 def _conv(args, filter_size, num_features, bias, bias_start=0.0):
2164   """Convolution.
2165 
2166   Args:
2167     args: a Tensor or a list of Tensors of dimension 3D, 4D or 5D,
2168     batch x n, Tensors.
2169     filter_size: int tuple of filter height and width.
2170     num_features: int, number of features.
2171     bias: Whether to use biases in the convolution layer.
2172     bias_start: starting value to initialize the bias; 0 by default.
2173 
2174   Returns:
2175     A 3D, 4D, or 5D Tensor with shape [batch ... num_features]
2176 
2177   Raises:
2178     ValueError: if some of the arguments has unspecified or wrong shape.
2179   """
2180 
2181   # Calculate the total size of arguments on dimension 1.
2182   total_arg_size_depth = 0
2183   shapes = [a.get_shape().as_list() for a in args]
2184   shape_length = len(shapes[0])
2185   for shape in shapes:
2186     if len(shape) not in [3, 4, 5]:
2187       raise ValueError("Conv Linear expects 3D, 4D "
2188                        "or 5D arguments: %s" % str(shapes))
2189     if len(shape) != len(shapes[0]):
2190       raise ValueError("Conv Linear expects all args "
2191                        "to be of same Dimension: %s" % str(shapes))
2192     else:
2193       total_arg_size_depth += shape[-1]
2194   dtype = [a.dtype for a in args][0]
2195 
2196   # determine correct conv operation
2197   if shape_length == 3:
2198     conv_op = nn_ops.conv1d
2199     strides = 1
2200   elif shape_length == 4:
2201     conv_op = nn_ops.conv2d
2202     strides = shape_length * [1]
2203   elif shape_length == 5:
2204     conv_op = nn_ops.conv3d
2205     strides = shape_length * [1]
2206 
2207   # Now the computation.
2208   kernel = vs.get_variable(
2209       "kernel", filter_size + [total_arg_size_depth, num_features], dtype=dtype)
2210   if len(args) == 1:
2211     res = conv_op(args[0], kernel, strides, padding="SAME")
2212   else:
2213     res = conv_op(
2214         array_ops.concat(axis=shape_length - 1, values=args),
2215         kernel,
2216         strides,
2217         padding="SAME")
2218   if not bias:
2219     return res
2220   bias_term = vs.get_variable(
2221       "biases", [num_features],
2222       dtype=dtype,
2223       initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(bias_start, dtype=dtype))
2224   return res + bias_term
2225 
2226 
2227 class GLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
2228   """Group LSTM cell (G-LSTM).
2229 
2230   The implementation is based on:
2231 
2232     https://arxiv.org/abs/1703.10722
2233 
2234   O. Kuchaiev and B. Ginsburg
2235   "Factorization Tricks for LSTM Networks", ICLR 2017 workshop.
2236 
2237   In brief, a G-LSTM cell consists of one LSTM sub-cell per group, where each
2238   sub-cell operates on an evenly-sized sub-vector of the input and produces an
2239   evenly-sized sub-vector of the output.  For example, a G-LSTM cell with 128
2240   units and 4 groups consists of 4 LSTMs sub-cells with 32 units each.  If that
2241   G-LSTM cell is fed a 200-dim input, then each sub-cell receives a 50-dim part
2242   of the input and produces a 32-dim part of the output.
2243   """
2244 
2245   def __init__(self,
2246                num_units,
2247                initializer=None,
2248                num_proj=None,
2249                number_of_groups=1,
2250                forget_bias=1.0,
2251                activation=math_ops.tanh,
2252                reuse=None):
2253     """Initialize the parameters of G-LSTM cell.
2254 
2255     Args:
2256       num_units: int, The number of units in the G-LSTM cell
2257       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
2258         projection matrices.
2259       num_proj: (optional) int, The output dimensionality for the projection
2260         matrices.  If None, no projection is performed.
2261       number_of_groups: (optional) int, number of groups to use.
2262         If `number_of_groups` is 1, then it should be equivalent to LSTM cell
2263       forget_bias: Biases of the forget gate are initialized by default to 1
2264         in order to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning of
2265         the training.
2266       activation: Activation function of the inner states.
2267       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
2268         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already
2269         has the given variables, an error is raised.
2270 
2271     Raises:
2272       ValueError: If `num_units` or `num_proj` is not divisible by
2273         `number_of_groups`.
2274     """
2275     super(GLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
2276     self._num_units = num_units
2277     self._initializer = initializer
2278     self._num_proj = num_proj
2279     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
2280     self._activation = activation
2281     self._number_of_groups = number_of_groups
2282 
2283     if self._num_units % self._number_of_groups != 0:
2284       raise ValueError("num_units must be divisible by number_of_groups")
2285     if self._num_proj:
2286       if self._num_proj % self._number_of_groups != 0:
2287         raise ValueError("num_proj must be divisible by number_of_groups")
2288       self._group_shape = [
2289           int(self._num_proj / self._number_of_groups),
2290           int(self._num_units / self._number_of_groups)
2291       ]
2292     else:
2293       self._group_shape = [
2294           int(self._num_units / self._number_of_groups),
2295           int(self._num_units / self._number_of_groups)
2296       ]
2297 
2298     if num_proj:
2299       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_proj)
2300       self._output_size = num_proj
2301     else:
2302       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_units)
2303       self._output_size = num_units
2304     self._linear1 = [None] * number_of_groups
2305     self._linear2 = None
2306 
2307   @property
2308   def state_size(self):
2309     return self._state_size
2310 
2311   @property
2312   def output_size(self):
2313     return self._output_size
2314 
2315   def _get_input_for_group(self, inputs, group_id, group_size):
2316     """Slices inputs into groups to prepare for processing by cell's groups.
2317 
2318     Args:
2319       inputs: cell input or it's previous state,
2320               a Tensor, 2D, [batch x num_units]
2321       group_id: group id, a Scalar, for which to prepare input
2322       group_size: size of the group
2323 
2324     Returns:
2325       subset of inputs corresponding to group "group_id",
2326       a Tensor, 2D, [batch x num_units/number_of_groups]
2327     """
2328     return array_ops.slice(
2329         input_=inputs,
2330         begin=[0, group_id * group_size],
2331         size=[self._batch_size, group_size],
2332         name=("GLSTM_group%d_input_generation" % group_id))
2333 
2334   def call(self, inputs, state):
2335     """Run one step of G-LSTM.
2336 
2337     Args:
2338       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, [batch x num_inputs].  num_inputs must be
2339         statically-known and evenly divisible into groups.  The innermost
2340         vectors of the inputs are split into evenly-sized sub-vectors and fed
2341         into the per-group LSTM sub-cells.
2342       state: this must be a tuple of state Tensors, both `2-D`, with column
2343         sizes `c_state` and `m_state`.
2344 
2345     Returns:
2346       A tuple containing:
2347 
2348       - A `2-D, [batch x output_dim]`, Tensor representing the output of the
2349         G-LSTM after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
2350         Here output_dim is:
2351            num_proj if num_proj was set,
2352            num_units otherwise.
2353       - LSTMStateTuple representing the new state of G-LSTM cell
2354         after reading `inputs` when the previous state was `state`.
2355 
2356     Raises:
2357       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
2358         static shape inference, or if the input shape is incompatible
2359         with the number of groups.
2360     """
2361     (c_prev, m_prev) = state
2362 
2363     self._batch_size = inputs.shape[0].value or array_ops.shape(inputs)[0]
2364 
2365     # If the input size is statically-known, calculate and validate its group
2366     # size.  Otherwise, use the output group size.
2367     input_size = inputs.shape[1].value
2368     if input_size is None:
2369       raise ValueError("input size must be statically known")
2370     if input_size % self._number_of_groups != 0:
2371       raise ValueError(
2372           "input size (%d) must be divisible by number_of_groups (%d)" %
2373           (input_size, self._number_of_groups))
2374     input_group_size = int(input_size / self._number_of_groups)
2375 
2376     dtype = inputs.dtype
2377     scope = vs.get_variable_scope()
2378     with vs.variable_scope(scope, initializer=self._initializer):
2379       i_parts = []
2380       j_parts = []
2381       f_parts = []
2382       o_parts = []
2383 
2384       for group_id in range(self._number_of_groups):
2385         with vs.variable_scope("group%d" % group_id):
2386           x_g_id = array_ops.concat(
2387               [
2388                   self._get_input_for_group(inputs, group_id, input_group_size),
2389                   self._get_input_for_group(m_prev, group_id,
2390                                             self._group_shape[0])
2391               ],
2392               axis=1)
2393           linear = self._linear1[group_id]
2394           if linear is None:
2395             linear = _Linear(x_g_id, 4 * self._group_shape[1], False)
2396             self._linear1[group_id] = linear
2397           R_k = linear(x_g_id)  # pylint: disable=invalid-name
2398           i_k, j_k, f_k, o_k = array_ops.split(R_k, 4, 1)
2399 
2400         i_parts.append(i_k)
2401         j_parts.append(j_k)
2402         f_parts.append(f_k)
2403         o_parts.append(o_k)
2404 
2405       bi = vs.get_variable(
2406           name="bias_i",
2407           shape=[self._num_units],
2408           dtype=dtype,
2409           initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype))
2410       bj = vs.get_variable(
2411           name="bias_j",
2412           shape=[self._num_units],
2413           dtype=dtype,
2414           initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype))
2415       bf = vs.get_variable(
2416           name="bias_f",
2417           shape=[self._num_units],
2418           dtype=dtype,
2419           initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype))
2420       bo = vs.get_variable(
2421           name="bias_o",
2422           shape=[self._num_units],
2423           dtype=dtype,
2424           initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype))
2425 
2426       i = nn_ops.bias_add(array_ops.concat(i_parts, axis=1), bi)
2427       j = nn_ops.bias_add(array_ops.concat(j_parts, axis=1), bj)
2428       f = nn_ops.bias_add(array_ops.concat(f_parts, axis=1), bf)
2429       o = nn_ops.bias_add(array_ops.concat(o_parts, axis=1), bo)
2430 
2431     c = (
2432         math_ops.sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias) * c_prev +
2433         math_ops.sigmoid(i) * math_ops.tanh(j))
2434     m = math_ops.sigmoid(o) * self._activation(c)
2435 
2436     if self._num_proj is not None:
2437       with vs.variable_scope("projection"):
2438         if self._linear2 is None:
2439           self._linear2 = _Linear(m, self._num_proj, False)
2440         m = self._linear2(m)
2441 
2442     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(c, m)
2443     return m, new_state
2444 
2445 
2446 class LayerNormLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
2447   """Long short-term memory unit (LSTM) recurrent network cell.
2448 
2449   The default non-peephole implementation is based on:
2450 
2451     https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/1154/0131eae85b2e11d53df7f1360eeb6476e7f4.pdf
2452 
2453   Felix Gers, Jurgen Schmidhuber, and Fred Cummins.
2454   "Learning to forget: Continual prediction with LSTM." IET, 850-855, 1999.
2455 
2456   The peephole implementation is based on:
2457 
2458     https://research.google.com/pubs/archive/43905.pdf
2459 
2460   Hasim Sak, Andrew Senior, and Francoise Beaufays.
2461   "Long short-term memory recurrent neural network architectures for
2462    large scale acoustic modeling." INTERSPEECH, 2014.
2463 
2464   The class uses optional peep-hole connections, optional cell clipping, and
2465   an optional projection layer.
2466 
2467   Layer normalization implementation is based on:
2468 
2469     https://arxiv.org/abs/1607.06450.
2470 
2471   "Layer Normalization"
2472   Jimmy Lei Ba, Jamie Ryan Kiros, Geoffrey E. Hinton
2473 
2474   and is applied before the internal nonlinearities.
2475 
2476   """
2477 
2478   def __init__(self,
2479                num_units,
2480                use_peepholes=False,
2481                cell_clip=None,
2482                initializer=None,
2483                num_proj=None,
2484                proj_clip=None,
2485                forget_bias=1.0,
2486                activation=None,
2487                layer_norm=False,
2488                norm_gain=1.0,
2489                norm_shift=0.0,
2490                reuse=None):
2491     """Initialize the parameters for an LSTM cell.
2492 
2493     Args:
2494       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
2495       use_peepholes: bool, set True to enable diagonal/peephole connections.
2496       cell_clip: (optional) A float value, if provided the cell state is clipped
2497         by this value prior to the cell output activation.
2498       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight and
2499         projection matrices.
2500       num_proj: (optional) int, The output dimensionality for the projection
2501         matrices.  If None, no projection is performed.
2502       proj_clip: (optional) A float value.  If `num_proj > 0` and `proj_clip` is
2503         provided, then the projected values are clipped elementwise to within
2504         `[-proj_clip, proj_clip]`.
2505       forget_bias: Biases of the forget gate are initialized by default to 1
2506         in order to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning of
2507         the training. Must set it manually to `0.0` when restoring from
2508         CudnnLSTM trained checkpoints.
2509       activation: Activation function of the inner states.  Default: `tanh`.
2510       layer_norm: If `True`, layer normalization will be applied.
2511       norm_gain: float, The layer normalization gain initial value. If
2512         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
2513       norm_shift: float, The layer normalization shift initial value. If
2514         `layer_norm` has been set to `False`, this argument will be ignored.
2515       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
2516         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
2517         the given variables, an error is raised.
2518 
2519       When restoring from CudnnLSTM-trained checkpoints, must use
2520       CudnnCompatibleLSTMCell instead.
2521     """
2522     super(LayerNormLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
2523 
2524     self._num_units = num_units
2525     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
2526     self._cell_clip = cell_clip
2527     self._initializer = initializer
2528     self._num_proj = num_proj
2529     self._proj_clip = proj_clip
2530     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
2531     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
2532     self._layer_norm = layer_norm
2533     self._norm_gain = norm_gain
2534     self._norm_shift = norm_shift
2535 
2536     if num_proj:
2537       self._state_size = (rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_proj))
2538       self._output_size = num_proj
2539     else:
2540       self._state_size = (rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_units))
2541       self._output_size = num_units
2542 
2543   @property
2544   def state_size(self):
2545     return self._state_size
2546 
2547   @property
2548   def output_size(self):
2549     return self._output_size
2550 
2551   def _linear(self,
2552               args,
2553               output_size,
2554               bias,
2555               bias_initializer=None,
2556               kernel_initializer=None,
2557               layer_norm=False):
2558     """Linear map: sum_i(args[i] * W[i]), where W[i] is a Variable.
2559 
2560     Args:
2561       args: a 2D Tensor or a list of 2D, batch x n, Tensors.
2562       output_size: int, second dimension of W[i].
2563       bias: boolean, whether to add a bias term or not.
2564       bias_initializer: starting value to initialize the bias
2565         (default is all zeros).
2566       kernel_initializer: starting value to initialize the weight.
2567       layer_norm: boolean, whether to apply layer normalization.
2568 
2569 
2570     Returns:
2571       A 2D Tensor with shape [batch x output_size] taking value
2572       sum_i(args[i] * W[i]), where each W[i] is a newly created Variable.
2573 
2574     Raises:
2575       ValueError: if some of the arguments has unspecified or wrong shape.
2576     """
2577     if args is None or (nest.is_sequence(args) and not args):
2578       raise ValueError("`args` must be specified")
2579     if not nest.is_sequence(args):
2580       args = [args]
2581 
2582     # Calculate the total size of arguments on dimension 1.
2583     total_arg_size = 0
2584     shapes = [a.get_shape() for a in args]
2585     for shape in shapes:
2586       if shape.ndims != 2:
2587         raise ValueError("linear is expecting 2D arguments: %s" % shapes)
2588       if shape[1].value is None:
2589         raise ValueError("linear expects shape[1] to be provided for shape %s, "
2590                          "but saw %s" % (shape, shape[1]))
2591       else:
2592         total_arg_size += shape[1].value
2593 
2594     dtype = [a.dtype for a in args][0]
2595 
2596     # Now the computation.
2597     scope = vs.get_variable_scope()
2598     with vs.variable_scope(scope) as outer_scope:
2599       weights = vs.get_variable(
2600           "kernel", [total_arg_size, output_size],
2601           dtype=dtype,
2602           initializer=kernel_initializer)
2603       if len(args) == 1:
2604         res = math_ops.matmul(args[0], weights)
2605       else:
2606         res = math_ops.matmul(array_ops.concat(args, 1), weights)
2607       if not bias:
2608         return res
2609       with vs.variable_scope(outer_scope) as inner_scope:
2610         inner_scope.set_partitioner(None)
2611         if bias_initializer is None:
2612           bias_initializer = init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype)
2613         biases = vs.get_variable(
2614             "bias", [output_size], dtype=dtype, initializer=bias_initializer)
2615 
2616     if not layer_norm:
2617       res = nn_ops.bias_add(res, biases)
2618 
2619     return res
2620 
2621   def call(self, inputs, state):
2622     """Run one step of LSTM.
2623 
2624     Args:
2625       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
2626       state: this must be a tuple of state Tensors,
2627        both `2-D`, with column sizes `c_state` and
2628         `m_state`.
2629 
2630     Returns:
2631       A tuple containing:
2632 
2633       - A `2-D, [batch x output_dim]`, Tensor representing the output of the
2634         LSTM after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
2635         Here output_dim is:
2636            num_proj if num_proj was set,
2637            num_units otherwise.
2638       - Tensor(s) representing the new state of LSTM after reading `inputs` when
2639         the previous state was `state`.  Same type and shape(s) as `state`.
2640 
2641     Raises:
2642       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
2643         static shape inference.
2644     """
2645     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
2646 
2647     (c_prev, m_prev) = state
2648 
2649     dtype = inputs.dtype
2650     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
2651     if input_size.value is None:
2652       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
2653     scope = vs.get_variable_scope()
2654     with vs.variable_scope(scope, initializer=self._initializer) as unit_scope:
2655 
2656       # i = input_gate, j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
2657       lstm_matrix = self._linear(
2658           [inputs, m_prev],
2659           4 * self._num_units,
2660           bias=True,
2661           bias_initializer=None,
2662           layer_norm=self._layer_norm)
2663       i, j, f, o = array_ops.split(
2664           value=lstm_matrix, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
2665 
2666       if self._layer_norm:
2667         i = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, i, "input")
2668         j = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, j, "transform")
2669         f = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, f, "forget")
2670         o = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, o, "output")
2671 
2672       # Diagonal connections
2673       if self._use_peepholes:
2674         with vs.variable_scope(unit_scope):
2675           w_f_diag = vs.get_variable(
2676               "w_f_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
2677           w_i_diag = vs.get_variable(
2678               "w_i_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
2679           w_o_diag = vs.get_variable(
2680               "w_o_diag", shape=[self._num_units], dtype=dtype)
2681 
2682       if self._use_peepholes:
2683         c = (
2684             sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag * c_prev) * c_prev +
2685             sigmoid(i + w_i_diag * c_prev) * self._activation(j))
2686       else:
2687         c = (
2688             sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias) * c_prev +
2689             sigmoid(i) * self._activation(j))
2690 
2691       if self._layer_norm:
2692         c = _norm(self._norm_gain, self._norm_shift, c, "state")
2693 
2694       if self._cell_clip is not None:
2695         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2696         c = clip_ops.clip_by_value(c, -self._cell_clip, self._cell_clip)
2697         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2698       if self._use_peepholes:
2699         m = sigmoid(o + w_o_diag * c) * self._activation(c)
2700       else:
2701         m = sigmoid(o) * self._activation(c)
2702 
2703       if self._num_proj is not None:
2704         with vs.variable_scope("projection"):
2705           m = self._linear(m, self._num_proj, bias=False)
2706 
2707         if self._proj_clip is not None:
2708           # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2709           m = clip_ops.clip_by_value(m, -self._proj_clip, self._proj_clip)
2710           # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2711 
2712     new_state = (rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(c, m))
2713     return m, new_state
2714 
2715 
2716 class SRUCell(rnn_cell_impl.LayerRNNCell):
2717   """SRU, Simple Recurrent Unit.
2718 
2719      Implementation based on
2720      Training RNNs as Fast as CNNs (cf. https://arxiv.org/abs/1709.02755).
2721 
2722      This variation of RNN cell is characterized by the simplified data
2723      dependence
2724      between hidden states of two consecutive time steps. Traditionally, hidden
2725      states from a cell at time step t-1 needs to be multiplied with a matrix
2726      W_hh before being fed into the ensuing cell at time step t.
2727      This flavor of RNN replaces the matrix multiplication between h_{t-1}
2728      and W_hh with a pointwise multiplication, resulting in performance
2729      gain.
2730 
2731   Args:
2732     num_units: int, The number of units in the SRU cell.
2733     activation: Nonlinearity to use.  Default: `tanh`.
2734     reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
2735       in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
2736       the given variables, an error is raised.
2737     name: (optional) String, the name of the layer. Layers with the same name
2738       will share weights, but to avoid mistakes we require reuse=True in such
2739       cases.
2740   """
2741 
2742   def __init__(self, num_units, activation=None, reuse=None, name=None):
2743     super(SRUCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse, name=name)
2744     self._num_units = num_units
2745     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
2746 
2747     # Restrict inputs to be 2-dimensional matrices
2748     self.input_spec = base_layer.InputSpec(ndim=2)
2749 
2750   @property
2751   def state_size(self):
2752     return self._num_units
2753 
2754   @property
2755   def output_size(self):
2756     return self._num_units
2757 
2758   def build(self, inputs_shape):
2759     if inputs_shape[1].value is None:
2760       raise ValueError(
2761           "Expected inputs.shape[-1] to be known, saw shape: %s" % inputs_shape)
2762 
2763     input_depth = inputs_shape[1].value
2764 
2765     # pylint: disable=protected-access
2766     self._kernel = self.add_variable(
2767         rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
2768         shape=[input_depth, 4 * self._num_units])
2769     # pylint: enable=protected-access
2770     self._bias = self.add_variable(
2771         rnn_cell_impl._BIAS_VARIABLE_NAME,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2772         shape=[2 * self._num_units],
2773         initializer=init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=self.dtype))
2774 
2775     self._built = True
2776 
2777   def call(self, inputs, state):
2778     """Simple recurrent unit (SRU) with num_units cells."""
2779 
2780     U = math_ops.matmul(inputs, self._kernel)  # pylint: disable=invalid-name
2781     x_bar, f_intermediate, r_intermediate, x_tx = array_ops.split(
2782         value=U, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
2783 
2784     f_r = math_ops.sigmoid(
2785         nn_ops.bias_add(
2786             array_ops.concat([f_intermediate, r_intermediate], 1), self._bias))
2787     f, r = array_ops.split(value=f_r, num_or_size_splits=2, axis=1)
2788 
2789     c = f * state + (1.0 - f) * x_bar
2790     h = r * self._activation(c) + (1.0 - r) * x_tx
2791 
2792     return h, c
2793 
2794 
2795 class WeightNormLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
2796   """Weight normalized LSTM Cell. Adapted from `rnn_cell_impl.LSTMCell`.
2797 
2798     The weight-norm implementation is based on:
2799     https://arxiv.org/abs/1602.07868
2800     Tim Salimans, Diederik P. Kingma.
2801     Weight Normalization: A Simple Reparameterization to Accelerate
2802     Training of Deep Neural Networks
2803 
2804     The default LSTM implementation based on:
2805 
2806       https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/1154/0131eae85b2e11d53df7f1360eeb6476e7f4.pdf
2807 
2808     Felix Gers, Jurgen Schmidhuber, and Fred Cummins.
2809     "Learning to forget: Continual prediction with LSTM." IET, 850-855, 1999.
2810 
2811     The class uses optional peephole connections, optional cell clipping
2812     and an optional projection layer.
2813 
2814     The optional peephole implementation is based on:
2815     https://research.google.com/pubs/archive/43905.pdf
2816     Hasim Sak, Andrew Senior, and Francoise Beaufays.
2817     "Long short-term memory recurrent neural network architectures for
2818     large scale acoustic modeling." INTERSPEECH, 2014.
2819   """
2820 
2821   def __init__(self,
2822                num_units,
2823                norm=True,
2824                use_peepholes=False,
2825                cell_clip=None,
2826                initializer=None,
2827                num_proj=None,
2828                proj_clip=None,
2829                forget_bias=1,
2830                activation=None,
2831                reuse=None):
2832     """Initialize the parameters of a weight-normalized LSTM cell.
2833 
2834     Args:
2835       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell
2836       norm: If `True`, apply normalization to the weight matrices. If False,
2837         the result is identical to that obtained from `rnn_cell_impl.LSTMCell`
2838       use_peepholes: bool, set `True` to enable diagonal/peephole connections.
2839       cell_clip: (optional) A float value, if provided the cell state is clipped
2840         by this value prior to the cell output activation.
2841       initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight matrices.
2842       num_proj: (optional) int, The output dimensionality for the projection
2843         matrices.  If None, no projection is performed.
2844       proj_clip: (optional) A float value.  If `num_proj > 0` and `proj_clip` is
2845         provided, then the projected values are clipped elementwise to within
2846         `[-proj_clip, proj_clip]`.
2847       forget_bias: Biases of the forget gate are initialized by default to 1
2848         in order to reduce the scale of forgetting at the beginning of
2849         the training.
2850       activation: Activation function of the inner states.  Default: `tanh`.
2851       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
2852         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
2853         the given variables, an error is raised.
2854     """
2855     super(WeightNormLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse)
2856 
2857     self._scope = "wn_lstm_cell"
2858     self._num_units = num_units
2859     self._norm = norm
2860     self._initializer = initializer
2861     self._use_peepholes = use_peepholes
2862     self._cell_clip = cell_clip
2863     self._num_proj = num_proj
2864     self._proj_clip = proj_clip
2865     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
2866     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
2867 
2868     self._weights_variable_name = "kernel"
2869     self._bias_variable_name = "bias"
2870 
2871     if num_proj:
2872       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_proj)
2873       self._output_size = num_proj
2874     else:
2875       self._state_size = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(num_units, num_units)
2876       self._output_size = num_units
2877 
2878   @property
2879   def state_size(self):
2880     return self._state_size
2881 
2882   @property
2883   def output_size(self):
2884     return self._output_size
2885 
2886   def _normalize(self, weight, name):
2887     """Apply weight normalization.
2888 
2889     Args:
2890       weight: a 2D tensor with known number of columns.
2891       name: string, variable name for the normalizer.
2892     Returns:
2893       A tensor with the same shape as `weight`.
2894     """
2895 
2896     output_size = weight.get_shape().as_list()[1]
2897     g = vs.get_variable(name, [output_size], dtype=weight.dtype)
2898     return nn_impl.l2_normalize(weight, axis=0) * g
2899 
2900   def _linear(self,
2901               args,
2902               output_size,
2903               norm,
2904               bias,
2905               bias_initializer=None,
2906               kernel_initializer=None):
2907     """Linear map: sum_i(args[i] * W[i]), where W[i] is a variable.
2908 
2909     Args:
2910       args: a 2D Tensor or a list of 2D, batch x n, Tensors.
2911       output_size: int, second dimension of W[i].
2912       norm: bool, whether to normalize the weights.
2913       bias: boolean, whether to add a bias term or not.
2914       bias_initializer: starting value to initialize the bias
2915         (default is all zeros).
2916       kernel_initializer: starting value to initialize the weight.
2917 
2918     Returns:
2919       A 2D Tensor with shape [batch x output_size] equal to
2920       sum_i(args[i] * W[i]), where W[i]s are newly created matrices.
2921 
2922     Raises:
2923       ValueError: if some of the arguments has unspecified or wrong shape.
2924     """
2925     if args is None or (nest.is_sequence(args) and not args):
2926       raise ValueError("`args` must be specified")
2927     if not nest.is_sequence(args):
2928       args = [args]
2929 
2930     # Calculate the total size of arguments on dimension 1.
2931     total_arg_size = 0
2932     shapes = [a.get_shape() for a in args]
2933     for shape in shapes:
2934       if shape.ndims != 2:
2935         raise ValueError("linear is expecting 2D arguments: %s" % shapes)
2936       if shape[1].value is None:
2937         raise ValueError("linear expects shape[1] to be provided for shape %s, "
2938                          "but saw %s" % (shape, shape[1]))
2939       else:
2940         total_arg_size += shape[1].value
2941 
2942     dtype = [a.dtype for a in args][0]
2943 
2944     # Now the computation.
2945     scope = vs.get_variable_scope()
2946     with vs.variable_scope(scope) as outer_scope:
2947       weights = vs.get_variable(
2948           self._weights_variable_name, [total_arg_size, output_size],
2949           dtype=dtype,
2950           initializer=kernel_initializer)
2951       if norm:
2952         wn = []
2953         st = 0
2954         with ops.control_dependencies(None):
2955           for i in range(len(args)):
2956             en = st + shapes[i][1].value
2957             wn.append(
2958                 self._normalize(weights[st:en, :], name="norm_{}".format(i)))
2959             st = en
2960 
2961           weights = array_ops.concat(wn, axis=0)
2962 
2963       if len(args) == 1:
2964         res = math_ops.matmul(args[0], weights)
2965       else:
2966         res = math_ops.matmul(array_ops.concat(args, 1), weights)
2967       if not bias:
2968         return res
2969 
2970       with vs.variable_scope(outer_scope) as inner_scope:
2971         inner_scope.set_partitioner(None)
2972         if bias_initializer is None:
2973           bias_initializer = init_ops.constant_initializer(0.0, dtype=dtype)
2974 
2975         biases = vs.get_variable(
2976             self._bias_variable_name, [output_size],
2977             dtype=dtype,
2978             initializer=bias_initializer)
2979 
2980       return nn_ops.bias_add(res, biases)
2981 
2982   def call(self, inputs, state):
2983     """Run one step of LSTM.
2984 
2985     Args:
2986       inputs: input Tensor, 2D, batch x num_units.
2987       state: A tuple of state Tensors, both `2-D`, with column sizes
2988        `c_state` and `m_state`.
2989 
2990     Returns:
2991       A tuple containing:
2992 
2993       - A `2-D, [batch x output_dim]`, Tensor representing the output of the
2994         LSTM after reading `inputs` when previous state was `state`.
2995         Here output_dim is:
2996            num_proj if num_proj was set,
2997            num_units otherwise.
2998       - Tensor(s) representing the new state of LSTM after reading `inputs` when
2999         the previous state was `state`.  Same type and shape(s) as `state`.
3000 
3001     Raises:
3002       ValueError: If input size cannot be inferred from inputs via
3003         static shape inference.
3004     """
3005     dtype = inputs.dtype
3006     num_units = self._num_units
3007     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
3008     c, h = state
3009 
3010     input_size = inputs.get_shape().with_rank(2)[1]
3011     if input_size.value is None:
3012       raise ValueError("Could not infer input size from inputs.get_shape()[-1]")
3013 
3014     with vs.variable_scope(self._scope, initializer=self._initializer):
3015 
3016       concat = self._linear(
3017           [inputs, h], 4 * num_units, norm=self._norm, bias=True)
3018 
3019       # i = input_gate, j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
3020       i, j, f, o = array_ops.split(value=concat, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
3021 
3022       if self._use_peepholes:
3023         w_f_diag = vs.get_variable("w_f_diag", shape=[num_units], dtype=dtype)
3024         w_i_diag = vs.get_variable("w_i_diag", shape=[num_units], dtype=dtype)
3025         w_o_diag = vs.get_variable("w_o_diag", shape=[num_units], dtype=dtype)
3026 
3027         new_c = (
3028             c * sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias + w_f_diag * c) +
3029             sigmoid(i + w_i_diag * c) * self._activation(j))
3030       else:
3031         new_c = (
3032             c * sigmoid(f + self._forget_bias) +
3033             sigmoid(i) * self._activation(j))
3034 
3035       if self._cell_clip is not None:
3036         # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
3037         new_c = clip_ops.clip_by_value(new_c, -self._cell_clip, self._cell_clip)
3038         # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
3039       if self._use_peepholes:
3040         new_h = sigmoid(o + w_o_diag * new_c) * self._activation(new_c)
3041       else:
3042         new_h = sigmoid(o) * self._activation(new_c)
3043 
3044       if self._num_proj is not None:
3045         with vs.variable_scope("projection"):
3046           new_h = self._linear(
3047               new_h, self._num_proj, norm=self._norm, bias=False)
3048 
3049         if self._proj_clip is not None:
3050           # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
3051           new_h = clip_ops.clip_by_value(new_h, -self._proj_clip,
3052                                          self._proj_clip)
3053           # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
3054 
3055       new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_c, new_h)
3056       return new_h, new_state
3057 
3058 
3059 class IndRNNCell(rnn_cell_impl.LayerRNNCell):
3060   """Independently Recurrent Neural Network (IndRNN) cell
3061     (cf. https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.04831).
3062 
3063   Args:
3064     num_units: int, The number of units in the RNN cell.
3065     activation: Nonlinearity to use.  Default: `tanh`.
3066     reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
3067      in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
3068      the given variables, an error is raised.
3069     name: String, the name of the layer. Layers with the same name will
3070       share weights, but to avoid mistakes we require reuse=True in such
3071       cases.
3072     dtype: Default dtype of the layer (default of `None` means use the type
3073       of the first input). Required when `build` is called before `call`.
3074   """
3075 
3076   def __init__(self,
3077                num_units,
3078                activation=None,
3079                reuse=None,
3080                name=None,
3081                dtype=None):
3082     super(IndRNNCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse, name=name, dtype=dtype)
3083 
3084     # Inputs must be 2-dimensional.
3085     self.input_spec = base_layer.InputSpec(ndim=2)
3086 
3087     self._num_units = num_units
3088     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
3089 
3090   @property
3091   def state_size(self):
3092     return self._num_units
3093 
3094   @property
3095   def output_size(self):
3096     return self._num_units
3097 
3098   def build(self, inputs_shape):
3099     if inputs_shape[1].value is None:
3100       raise ValueError(
3101           "Expected inputs.shape[-1] to be known, saw shape: %s" % inputs_shape)
3102 
3103     input_depth = inputs_shape[1].value
3104     # pylint: disable=protected-access
3105     self._kernel_w = self.add_variable(
3106         "%s_w" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3107         shape=[input_depth, self._num_units])
3108     self._kernel_u = self.add_variable(
3109         "%s_u" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3110         shape=[1, self._num_units],
3111         initializer=init_ops.random_uniform_initializer(
3112             minval=-1, maxval=1, dtype=self.dtype))
3113     self._bias = self.add_variable(
3114         rnn_cell_impl._BIAS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3115         shape=[self._num_units],
3116         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(dtype=self.dtype))
3117     # pylint: enable=protected-access
3118 
3119     self.built = True
3120 
3121   def call(self, inputs, state):
3122     """IndRNN: output = new_state = act(W * input + u * state + B)."""
3123 
3124     gate_inputs = math_ops.matmul(inputs, self._kernel_w) + (
3125         state * self._kernel_u)
3126     gate_inputs = nn_ops.bias_add(gate_inputs, self._bias)
3127     output = self._activation(gate_inputs)
3128     return output, output
3129 
3130 
3131 class IndyGRUCell(rnn_cell_impl.LayerRNNCell):
3132   r"""Independently Gated Recurrent Unit cell.
3133 
3134   Based on IndRNNs (https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.04831) and similar to GRUCell,
3135   yet with the \(U_r\), \(U_z\), and \(U\) matrices in equations 5, 6, and
3136   8 of http://arxiv.org/abs/1406.1078 respectively replaced by diagonal
3137   matrices, i.e. a Hadamard product with a single vector:
3138 
3139     $$r_j = \sigma\left([\mathbf W_r\mathbf x]_j +
3140       [\mathbf u_r\circ \mathbf h_{(t-1)}]_j\right)$$
3141     $$z_j = \sigma\left([\mathbf W_z\mathbf x]_j +
3142       [\mathbf u_z\circ \mathbf h_{(t-1)}]_j\right)$$
3143     $$\tilde{h}^{(t)}_j = \phi\left([\mathbf W \mathbf x]_j +
3144       [\mathbf u \circ \mathbf r \circ \mathbf h_{(t-1)}]_j\right)$$
3145 
3146   where \(\circ\) denotes the Hadamard operator. This means that each IndyGRU
3147   node sees only its own state, as opposed to seeing all states in the same
3148   layer.
3149 
3150   TODO(gonnet): Write a paper describing this and add a reference here.
3151 
3152   Args:
3153     num_units: int, The number of units in the GRU cell.
3154     activation: Nonlinearity to use.  Default: `tanh`.
3155     reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
3156      in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
3157      the given variables, an error is raised.
3158     kernel_initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight
3159       matrices applied to the input.
3160     bias_initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the bias.
3161     name: String, the name of the layer. Layers with the same name will
3162       share weights, but to avoid mistakes we require reuse=True in such
3163       cases.
3164     dtype: Default dtype of the layer (default of `None` means use the type
3165       of the first input). Required when `build` is called before `call`.
3166   """
3167 
3168   def __init__(self,
3169                num_units,
3170                activation=None,
3171                reuse=None,
3172                kernel_initializer=None,
3173                bias_initializer=None,
3174                name=None,
3175                dtype=None):
3176     super(IndyGRUCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse, name=name, dtype=dtype)
3177 
3178     # Inputs must be 2-dimensional.
3179     self.input_spec = base_layer.InputSpec(ndim=2)
3180 
3181     self._num_units = num_units
3182     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
3183     self._kernel_initializer = kernel_initializer
3184     self._bias_initializer = bias_initializer
3185 
3186   @property
3187   def state_size(self):
3188     return self._num_units
3189 
3190   @property
3191   def output_size(self):
3192     return self._num_units
3193 
3194   def build(self, inputs_shape):
3195     if inputs_shape[1].value is None:
3196       raise ValueError(
3197           "Expected inputs.shape[-1] to be known, saw shape: %s" % inputs_shape)
3198 
3199     input_depth = inputs_shape[1].value
3200     # pylint: disable=protected-access
3201     self._gate_kernel_w = self.add_variable(
3202         "gates/%s_w" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3203         shape=[input_depth, 2 * self._num_units],
3204         initializer=self._kernel_initializer)
3205     self._gate_kernel_u = self.add_variable(
3206         "gates/%s_u" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3207         shape=[1, 2 * self._num_units],
3208         initializer=init_ops.random_uniform_initializer(
3209             minval=-1, maxval=1, dtype=self.dtype))
3210     self._gate_bias = self.add_variable(
3211         "gates/%s" % rnn_cell_impl._BIAS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3212         shape=[2 * self._num_units],
3213         initializer=(self._bias_initializer
3214                      if self._bias_initializer is not None else
3215                      init_ops.constant_initializer(1.0, dtype=self.dtype)))
3216     self._candidate_kernel_w = self.add_variable(
3217         "candidate/%s" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3218         shape=[input_depth, self._num_units],
3219         initializer=self._kernel_initializer)
3220     self._candidate_kernel_u = self.add_variable(
3221         "candidate/%s_u" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3222         shape=[1, self._num_units],
3223         initializer=init_ops.random_uniform_initializer(
3224             minval=-1, maxval=1, dtype=self.dtype))
3225     self._candidate_bias = self.add_variable(
3226         "candidate/%s" % rnn_cell_impl._BIAS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3227         shape=[self._num_units],
3228         initializer=(self._bias_initializer
3229                      if self._bias_initializer is not None else
3230                      init_ops.zeros_initializer(dtype=self.dtype)))
3231     # pylint: enable=protected-access
3232 
3233     self.built = True
3234 
3235   def call(self, inputs, state):
3236     """Gated recurrent unit (GRU) with nunits cells."""
3237 
3238     gate_inputs = math_ops.matmul(inputs, self._gate_kernel_w) + (
3239         gen_array_ops.tile(state, [1, 2]) * self._gate_kernel_u)
3240     gate_inputs = nn_ops.bias_add(gate_inputs, self._gate_bias)
3241 
3242     value = math_ops.sigmoid(gate_inputs)
3243     r, u = array_ops.split(value=value, num_or_size_splits=2, axis=1)
3244 
3245     r_state = r * state
3246 
3247     candidate = math_ops.matmul(inputs, self._candidate_kernel_w) + (
3248         r_state * self._candidate_kernel_u)
3249     candidate = nn_ops.bias_add(candidate, self._candidate_bias)
3250 
3251     c = self._activation(candidate)
3252     new_h = u * state + (1 - u) * c
3253     return new_h, new_h
3254 
3255 
3256 class IndyLSTMCell(rnn_cell_impl.LayerRNNCell):
3257   r"""Basic IndyLSTM recurrent network cell.
3258 
3259   Based on IndRNNs (https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.04831) and similar to
3260   BasicLSTMCell, yet with the \(U_f\), \(U_i\), \(U_o\) and \(U_c\)
3261   matrices in
3262   https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_short-term_memory#LSTM_with_a_forget_gate
3263   replaced by diagonal matrices, i.e. a Hadamard product with a single vector:
3264 
3265     $$f_t = \sigma_g\left(W_f x_t + u_f \circ h_{t-1} + b_f\right)$$
3266     $$i_t = \sigma_g\left(W_i x_t + u_i \circ h_{t-1} + b_i\right)$$
3267     $$o_t = \sigma_g\left(W_o x_t + u_o \circ h_{t-1} + b_o\right)$$
3268     $$c_t = f_t \circ c_{t-1} +
3269             i_t \circ \sigma_c\left(W_c x_t + u_c \circ h_{t-1} + b_c\right)$$
3270 
3271   where \(\circ\) denotes the Hadamard operator. This means that each IndyLSTM
3272   node sees only its own state \(h\) and \(c\), as opposed to seeing all
3273   states in the same layer.
3274 
3275   We add forget_bias (default: 1) to the biases of the forget gate in order to
3276   reduce the scale of forgetting in the beginning of the training.
3277 
3278   It does not allow cell clipping, a projection layer, and does not
3279   use peep-hole connections: it is the basic baseline.
3280 
3281   For advanced models, please use the full `tf.nn.rnn_cell.LSTMCell`
3282   that follows.
3283 
3284   TODO(gonnet): Write a paper describing this and add a reference here.
3285   """
3286 
3287   def __init__(self,
3288                num_units,
3289                forget_bias=1.0,
3290                activation=None,
3291                reuse=None,
3292                kernel_initializer=None,
3293                bias_initializer=None,
3294                name=None,
3295                dtype=None):
3296     """Initialize the IndyLSTM cell.
3297 
3298     Args:
3299       num_units: int, The number of units in the LSTM cell.
3300       forget_bias: float, The bias added to forget gates (see above).
3301         Must set to `0.0` manually when restoring from CudnnLSTM-trained
3302         checkpoints.
3303       activation: Activation function of the inner states.  Default: `tanh`.
3304       reuse: (optional) Python boolean describing whether to reuse variables
3305         in an existing scope.  If not `True`, and the existing scope already has
3306         the given variables, an error is raised.
3307       kernel_initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the weight
3308         matrix applied to the inputs.
3309       bias_initializer: (optional) The initializer to use for the bias.
3310       name: String, the name of the layer. Layers with the same name will
3311         share weights, but to avoid mistakes we require reuse=True in such
3312         cases.
3313       dtype: Default dtype of the layer (default of `None` means use the type
3314         of the first input). Required when `build` is called before `call`.
3315     """
3316     super(IndyLSTMCell, self).__init__(_reuse=reuse, name=name, dtype=dtype)
3317 
3318     # Inputs must be 2-dimensional.
3319     self.input_spec = base_layer.InputSpec(ndim=2)
3320 
3321     self._num_units = num_units
3322     self._forget_bias = forget_bias
3323     self._activation = activation or math_ops.tanh
3324     self._kernel_initializer = kernel_initializer
3325     self._bias_initializer = bias_initializer
3326 
3327   @property
3328   def state_size(self):
3329     return rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(self._num_units, self._num_units)
3330 
3331   @property
3332   def output_size(self):
3333     return self._num_units
3334 
3335   def build(self, inputs_shape):
3336     if inputs_shape[1].value is None:
3337       raise ValueError(
3338           "Expected inputs.shape[-1] to be known, saw shape: %s" % inputs_shape)
3339 
3340     input_depth = inputs_shape[1].value
3341     # pylint: disable=protected-access
3342     self._kernel_w = self.add_variable(
3343         "%s_w" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3344         shape=[input_depth, 4 * self._num_units],
3345         initializer=self._kernel_initializer)
3346     self._kernel_u = self.add_variable(
3347         "%s_u" % rnn_cell_impl._WEIGHTS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3348         shape=[1, 4 * self._num_units],
3349         initializer=init_ops.random_uniform_initializer(
3350             minval=-1, maxval=1, dtype=self.dtype))
3351     self._bias = self.add_variable(
3352         rnn_cell_impl._BIAS_VARIABLE_NAME,
3353         shape=[4 * self._num_units],
3354         initializer=(self._bias_initializer
3355                      if self._bias_initializer is not None else
3356                      init_ops.zeros_initializer(dtype=self.dtype)))
3357     # pylint: enable=protected-access
3358 
3359     self.built = True
3360 
3361   def call(self, inputs, state):
3362     """Independent Long short-term memory cell (IndyLSTM).
3363 
3364     Args:
3365       inputs: `2-D` tensor with shape `[batch_size, input_size]`.
3366       state: An `LSTMStateTuple` of state tensors, each shaped
3367         `[batch_size, num_units]`.
3368 
3369     Returns:
3370       A pair containing the new hidden state, and the new state (a
3371         `LSTMStateTuple`).
3372     """
3373     sigmoid = math_ops.sigmoid
3374     one = constant_op.constant(1, dtype=dtypes.int32)
3375     c, h = state
3376 
3377     gate_inputs = math_ops.matmul(inputs, self._kernel_w)
3378     gate_inputs += gen_array_ops.tile(h, [1, 4]) * self._kernel_u
3379     gate_inputs = nn_ops.bias_add(gate_inputs, self._bias)
3380 
3381     # i = input_gate, j = new_input, f = forget_gate, o = output_gate
3382     i, j, f, o = array_ops.split(
3383         value=gate_inputs, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=one)
3384 
3385     forget_bias_tensor = constant_op.constant(self._forget_bias, dtype=f.dtype)
3386     # Note that using `add` and `multiply` instead of `+` and `*` gives a
3387     # performance improvement. So using those at the cost of readability.
3388     add = math_ops.add
3389     multiply = math_ops.multiply
3390     new_c = add(
3391         multiply(c, sigmoid(add(f, forget_bias_tensor))),
3392         multiply(sigmoid(i), self._activation(j)))
3393     new_h = multiply(self._activation(new_c), sigmoid(o))
3394 
3395     new_state = rnn_cell_impl.LSTMStateTuple(new_c, new_h)
3396     return new_h, new_state
